0 @N00139@ NOTE geni:about_me SLAVERY IN MALTA
1 CONT <https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slavery_in_Malta>
1 CONT
1 CONT **Slave origin** « Approximately 80% of slaves were Muslim or Jewish. They
1 CONT were often captured during military conflicts by the Order and later during
1 CONT pirate raids. Muslim slaves were largely Turks, Moors, or Barbary pirates - as
1 CONT well as limited numbers of sub-Saharan Africans. Jews came from the Levant,
1 CONT the Aegean Islands, Rhodes, Crete, or Venice.[12] Around 20% were Christian,
1 CONT who came from Greece, the Middle East or Central Europe and may have already
1 CONT been slaves at the time of their capture. They would have to prove their
1 CONT religion before being freed from servitude, but they may have also remained
1 CONT slaves. Over time and according and dictated by need, Greeks were captured and
1 CONT held in slavery as schismatics,[14] or on the pretext that they would trade
1 CONT with the Turks.[15] This group also included new, former-Muslim converts (they
1 CONT were not liberated for converting), as well as renegades who had already
1 CONT changed their faith.[12] »
