0 @N00232@ NOTE geni:about_me -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/SICILY.htm#Beatricedied1307>
1 CONT
1 CONT 3\. ENRICO of Sicily (Trani May 1262-Castel dell'Uovo, Naples 31 Oct 1318).
1 CONT His birth is recorded in an anonymous chronicle of Trani[689], now apparently
1 CONT lost, which states that he was his mother's first child although this appears
1 CONT incorrect as there would be insufficient time during his mother's remaining
1 CONT period of married life to have given birth to four other children. After his
1 CONT capture with his mother at Trani following his father's death, Enrico was
1 CONT blinded and imprisoned in chains in the Castel del Monte, near Bari. A charter
1 CONT dated 9 Jan [1295] names "Henrici, Frederici ac Anselmi fratrum filiorum
1 CONT naturalium quondam Manfridi principis Tarentini in castri…sancte Marie de
1 CONT Monte Carcere"[690]. A charter dated 26 Apr [1297] names "Henricum Fredericum
1 CONT et Aczolinum filios quondam principis Manfridi qui in dicto Castro [=castri
1 CONT Sancte Marie de Monte]…detinentur"[691]. A charter dated 25 Jun 1299 names
1 CONT "Henricum Fredericum et Encium filios quondam Manfridi…principis
1 CONT Tarentini"[692]. Enrico was transferred to the Castel dell'Uovo in Naples in
1 CONT 1300 with his surviving brother[693].
