0 @N00261@ NOTE geni:about_me Son of King MANFRED von Hohenstaufen and his second wife.
1 CONT
1 CONT <http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/SICILY.htm#Beatricedied1307>
1 CONT
1 CONT 4\. FEDERICO of Sicily (-after 2 Jun 1312). He suffered the same fate as his
1 CONT brother Enrico. A charter dated 9 Jan [1295] names "Henrici, Frederici ac
1 CONT Anselmi fratrum filiorum naturalium quondam Manfridi principis Tarentini in
1 CONT castri…sancte Marie de Monte Carcere"[694]. A charter dated 26 Apr [1297]
1 CONT names "Henricum Fredericum et Aczolinum filios quondam principis Manfridi qui
1 CONT in dicto Castro [=castri Sancte Marie de Monte]…detinentur"[695]. A charter
1 CONT dated 25 Jun 1299 names "Henricum Fredericum et Encium filios quondam
1 CONT Manfridi…principis Tarentini"[696]. According to Haverkamp, he escaped from
1 CONT prison in the early 1300s, stayed at various European courts and supposedly
1 CONT died in Egypt in 1312[697].
1 CONT
1 CONT Medlands (and other sources I have seen) do not address the issue of whether,
1 CONT after his escape from prison; did Federico marry and have children?
1 CONT
1 CONT There are many on-line family trees that contend that he married Giovanna Di
1 CONT Antiochia and had a son and a daughter. I believe many (or all) of these
1 CONT references originate from an entry in Malta Genealology, a source of dubious
1 CONT quality. Still investigating.
1 CONT
1 CONT <https://www.maltagenealogy.com/hohenstaufen>
1 CONT
1 CONT 1.1.1.2.1.3.2. Federico di Siciliano, d.after 2 Jun 1312, married Giovanna di
1 CONT Antiochia, (See on this page), with issue.
1 CONT 1.1.1.2.1.3.2.1. Helene di Siciliano, 1305 - 48., married to Conradin von
1 CONT Sueva, (See on this page).
1 CONT 1.1.1.2.1.3.2.2. Manfredo di Siciliano 1303 - 51., married to Marianna di
1 CONT Chieti, (See on this page), with issue.
0 @N00262@ NOTE Adresse: Egypt, Egypt
0 @S00347@ SOUR
