0 @N00316@ NOTE geni:about_me ===Biography
1 CONT
1 CONT <https://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/corrado-iv_%28Federiciana%29/>
1 CONT
1 CONT Oltre al figlio nato dal suo matrimonio, C. lasciò ‒ come tanti altri suoi
1 CONT contemporanei ‒ un figlio naturale, anch'egli di nome **Corradino** , che
1 CONT tuttavia non svolse mai alcun ruolo di rilievo e fu giustiziato da Carlo
1 CONT d'Angiò nel 1269 dopo la capitolazione di Lucera.
1 CONT
1 CONT (Google translates)
1 CONT
1 CONT In addition to the son born of his marriage, C. left - like many other
1 CONT contemporaries - a natural son, also named Corradino, who nevertheless never
1 CONT played any important role and was executed by Charles of Anjou in 1269 after
1 CONT the capitulation of Lucera.
1 CONT
1 CONT \-------------
1 CONT
1 CONT ===Pedigree report
1 CONT
1 CONT <https://www.maltagenealogy.com/component/tags/tag/sillato>
1 CONT
1 CONT 1.1.1.2.1.2. Konrad IV, German King (b.Andria 1228, d.nr Lavello 1254);
1 CONT m.Vohburg 1246 Elisabeth (1227-1273) dau.of Duke Otto of Bavaria
1 CONT
1 CONT 1.1.1.2.1.2.1. Konradin, King of Sicily, Duke of Swabia (b.Burg Wolfstein
1 CONT 1252, beheaded at Naples 1268)
1 CONT
1 CONT **1.1.1.2.1.2.2. [illegitimate] Konradin von Sveva, hanged at Lucera 1269.,
1 CONT married to Margarita di San Lorenzo, with issue.
1 CONT **
1 CONT
1 CONT 1.1.1.2.1.2.2.1. Attilda von Sveva, married to Pietro Luca de Perrigrino, (son
1 CONT of Gerrardo de Perregrino, Capitano della Malta 1348-1350), with issue.
1 CONT
1 CONT ===Genealogy
1 CONT
1 CONT <http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/GERMANY,%20Kings.htm#KonradSwabiadied1268>
1 CONT
1 CONT King Konrad had one illegitimate son by Mistress (1): ---. The name of King
1 CONT Konrad's mistress is not known. Benoist-Méchin says that she was a Sarracin
1 CONT from Lucera but does not cite the corresponding primary source[703].
1 CONT
1 CONT b) KONRADIN (Lucera [1252]-hanged Lucera 1269). The primary source which
1 CONT confirms his parentage has not yet been identified. He was captured by Charles
1 CONT I King of Sicily [Anjou-Capet] at the siege of Lucera
