1 CONT [edit]Death and legacy
1 CONT
1 CONT Peter died at Vilafranca del Penedès on 2 November 1285, in the same year as
1 CONT his two royal foes, Charles and Philip, and was buried in the monastery of
1 CONT Santes Creus. His deathbed absolution occurred after he declared that his
1 CONT conquests had been in the name of his familial claims and never against the
1 CONT claims of the church.
1 CONT
1 CONT Peter left Aragon to his eldest son Alfonso III and Sicily to his second son
1 CONT James II. Peter's third son, Frederick III, in succession to his brother
1 CONT James, became regent of Sicily and in due course its king. Peter did not
1 CONT provide for his youngest son and namesake (1275 – 25 August 1296), who married
1 CONT Guillemette, daughter of Gaston VI of Béarn.
1 CONT
1 CONT Peter also had two daughters, Elisabeth, who married Denis of Portugal, and
1 CONT Yolanda (1273 – August 1302), who married Robert of Naples.
1 CONT
