1 CONT History: Pedro III (of Aragón)
1 CONT
1 CONT Pedro III (of Aragón) (1239-1285), king of Aragón (1276-1285), called the
1 CONT Great. Pedro was the son of James I and Yolande of Hungary. He conquered
1 CONT Sicily from Charles of Anjou in 1282 and repelled a French invasion of
1 CONT Catalonia in 1285\. Pedro’s reign marked the beginning of the long struggle
1 CONT between the Aragonese and Angevin dynasties.
