0 @N00343@ NOTE geni:about_me \- <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boniface_of_Verona>
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT \- <http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/bonifacio-da-verona_(Dizionario-
1 CONT Biografico)/>
1 CONT
1 CONT È ben possibile che il D. fosse un cavaliere povero che giunse alla corte di
1 CONT Guy de la Roche intorno al 1287. fu favorito dal duca, ricevette in moglie una
1 CONT pupilla di questo - la quale forse si chiamava **Simona** /!\
1 CONT
1 CONT \-----------------
1 CONT
1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/LATIN%20LORDSHIPS%20IN%20GREECE.htm#BonifazioVeronaEuboeadied1317>
1 CONT
1 CONT 3\. BONIFAZIO da Verona (-1317). His parentage is confirmed by the Istoria of
1 CONT Marino Sanudo Torsello which names "miser Francesco da Verona padre de miser
1 CONT Bonifacio"[594]. Guy II Duke of Athens granted him a revenue of 50,000 sols,
1 CONT his own mother's dowry of Gardiki in Thessaly and the island of Salamis, and
1 CONT arranged his marriage at the ceremony of his coming of age in 1294[595]. He
1 CONT recaptured Karistos from the Greeks, establishing himself as Triarch of Eubœa
1 CONT (northern part) in 1296[596]. The Istoria of Marino Sanudo Torsello records
1 CONT that "miser Bonifacio da Verona, figlio de miser Francesco" acquired "il
1 CONT castel di Caristo…per sua consorte"[597].
1 CONT
1 CONT \- EUBŒA - TRIARCHATE (NORTHERN PART). /!\
1 CONT
1 CONT \- - - - - -
1 CONT
1 CONT /!\
1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/LATIN%20LORDSHIPS%20IN%20GREECE.htm#BonifazioVeronaEuboeadied1317B>
1 CONT
1 CONT BONIFAZIO da Verona Lord of 1/3 Eubœa, son of GUGLIELMO [II] da Verona Lord of
1 CONT 1/3 Eubœa & his wife --- (-1317). Guy II Duke of Athens granted him a revenue
1 CONT of 50,000 sols, his own mother's dowry of Gardiki in Thessaly and the island
1 CONT of Salamis, and arranged his marriage at the ceremony of his coming of age in
1 CONT 1294[518]. He recaptured Karistos from the Greeks, establishing himself as
1 CONT Triarch of Eubœa (northern part) in 1296[519]. Duke Guy appointed Bonifazio as
1 CONT temporary administrator of the duchy of Athens when he died[520]. He fought at
1 CONT Kephissos River, near Thebes 15 Mar 1311 against the Catalans, but the latter
1 CONT asked him to be their leader after the battle, which he refused[521]. "Ser
1 CONT Bonifacius de Verona, dominator Caristi et Gardichie, Selizirij et Egue" is
1 CONT included in the list of Barons "de Romania" with whom Venice maintained
1 CONT relations in 1313[522].
1 CONT
1 CONT m AGNES de Cicon, daughter of GUY de Cicon Titular Triarch of Eubœa (northern
1 CONT part) & his wife ---. The Istoria of Marino Sanudo Torsello records that
1 CONT "miser Bonifacio da Verona, figlio de miser Francesco" acquired "il castel di
1 CONT Caristo…per sua consorte"[523]. The primary source which confirms her name has
1 CONT not yet been identified.
1 CONT
1 CONT Bonifazio & his wife had two children:
