0 @N00347@ NOTE (Riccardo di Teate count of Chieti)
0 @N00348@ NOTE geni:about_me -<https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riccardo_di_Teate>
1 CONT
1 CONT Richard of Chieti (Italian: Riccardo , * between 1222 and 1225, † May 1249 )
1 CONT was an illegitimate son of the Roman Emperor and King of Sicily, Frederick II
1 CONT of Hohenstaufen . His mother was a niece of Archbishop Berardus of Messina.
1 CONT
1 CONT From his father Richard was loaned in 1245 with the county Chieti . In the
1 CONT autumn of 1247, in the midst of the struggle against the Pope, he was
1 CONT appointed Vicar General of Mark Ancona and the Duchy of Spoleto . In December
1 CONT of the same year he beat a papal army at Terni under the leadership of Hugo
1 CONT Novellus. This he struck again in April 1248 at Civitanova Marche , killed him
1 CONT and the traitors Pandolf da Fasanella and Jacob da Morra. The news of this
1 CONT victory reached his father on April 20, 1248 in Borgo San Donnino (now Fidenza
1 CONT ), which he was very pleased, although this victory the emperor's heavy defeat
1 CONT before Parma few months ago could not outweigh.
1 CONT
1 CONT From the Chronica majora of Matthew Paris is the news of Richard's death,
1 CONT which was recorded immediately after the capture of his brother Enzio by the
1 CONT Bolognese after the Battle of Fossalta (May 26, 1249). Maybe Richard fell in
1 CONT the same battle.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Illegitimate son of Friedrich II von Hohenstaufen
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Più sicura appare l'identità della madre di Riccardo di Teate (o di Chieti), vicario generale della Marca e di Spoleto nato nel 1224/1225 e morto nella seconda metà del 1249: Manna, nipote del potente arcivescovo di Palermo Berardo di Castagna.
1 CONT
1 CONT   * <http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/GERMANY,%20Kings.htm#_ftnref663> \- Mistress (8): [MANNA, niece of --- Archbishop of Messina, daughter of ---. Benoist-Méchin says that the mother of **Riccardo Conte di Chieti** was "semble-t-il, le fils de Man
1 CONC na, une nièce de l´archévêque de Messine" but cites no corresponding source[663].]
1 CONT
1 CONT   * [https://gw.geneanet.org/jpbuhagiar?lang=en&pz=jean+pierre+baptiste+marcel&nz=buhagiar&p=riccardo&n=di+chieti+de+teate](https://gw.geneanet.org/jpbuhagiar?lang=en&pz=jean+pierre+baptiste+marcel&nz=buhagiar&p=riccardo&n=di+chieti+de+teate)
