1 CONT Charles III
1 CONT His 5 children went on to spread the royalty of Europe when Charles carefully
1 CONT built up an extremely complex set of alliances through the marriages of the
1 CONT children, thereby extending control over other territories. He was extremely
1 CONT pius & enlightened, a patron of the arts and a builder of monasteries and
1 CONT churches. He finally agreed to give up his battle to recover Sicily to his
1 CONT kingdom from the Aragonese, who would go on to rule Sicily for nearly 300
1 CONT years to the War of the Spanish Succession. (Sicily was lost in 1282).
