1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/MONFERRATO,%20SALUZZO,%20SAVONA.htm#BiancaLanciaMistrEmpFriedrich>
1 CONT
1 CONT c) BIANCA Lancia ([1205/12][804]-[1233/34]). The Thomas Tusci Gesta
1 CONT Imperatorum et Pontificum refers to the mother of "Manfredus" as "sorore
1 CONT marchionis Lancee…filia domne Blanca"[805]. The Historia Sicula of Bartolomeo
1 CONT di Neocastro names "domina Blanca…de Lancea de Lombardia" as the fifth wife of
1 CONT "dominus Fridericus secundus…Romanorum…imperator"[806]. The Historia
1 CONT Manuscrita Mediolanensi records that Emperor Friedrich II married "filiam
1 CONT Bonefacii Castellani" by whom he fathered "Regem Manfredum"[807]. A
1 CONT "confirmatio matrimonii in articulo mortis" in [1233/34] is recorded by
1 CONT Matthew of Paris, in the form of a declaration of her son Manfred[808]. The
1 CONT Cronica Fratris Salimbene de Adam refers to the mother of "Manfredus…filius
1 CONT Friderici" as "marchionis Lancee neptis", specifying that she married the
1 CONT Emperor "in obitu"[809].
1 CONT
1 CONT **Mistress** ([1231/34]) of Emperor FRIEDRICH II, son of Emperor HEINRICH VI &
1 CONT his wife Constance of Sicily (Iesi, Ancona 26 Dec 1194-Castel Fiorentino near
1 CONT Lucera, Foggia, 13 Dec 1250, bur 25 Feb 1251 Palermo Cathedral).
1 CONT
1 CONT \-----------
1 CONT \- <http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/bianca-lancia_%28Dizionario-
1 CONT Biografico%29/>
1 CONT
1 CONT \- <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bianca_Lancia>
1 CONT
1 CONT Possibly born in Agliano in Piedmont, where her ancestors of the Ghibelline
1 CONT Lancia (or Lanza) noble family, so-called since Manfred I (fl. 1160–1214) had
1 CONT been lancifer pikeman of Emperor Frederick Barbarossa, served as margraves.
1 CONT There is no source which definitively states who her parents were, historians
1 CONT have offered three theories that she was a granddaughter of Manfred I Lancia:
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   1. as daughter of his daughter (maybe also named Bianca), by a son (name unknown) of Guglielmo di Moncucco and Belda di Agliano.
1 CONT
1 CONT   2. as daughter of his son Bonifacio di Agliano by an unknown wife.
1 CONT
1 CONT   3. **as daughter of his son Manfred II, possible from a marriage to a lady called Bianca, of the Maletta family.** **If she was a daughter of Manfred II, she had seven siblings: four brothers (Manfred III, Guglielmo, Galvano and Frederick) and th
1 CONC ree sisters (Beatrice, Agnes and Isabella).**
1 CONT \----------
1 CONT Bianca Von Hohenstaufen (born Lanza) MyHeritage Family Trees Parents:
1 CONT Bonifacio Ier Lanza, Constanza Maletta Brother: Galvano Lanza Husband:
1 CONT Friedrich Ii Von Hohenstaufen Son: Manfred Von Hohenstaufen
1 CONT
1 CONT \---------
1 CONT Bianca Lancia d'Agliano (also called Beatrice and Blanche); was an Italian
1 CONT noblewoman, who was the mistress and later wife of emperor Frederick II of
1 CONT Hohenstaufen, although the marriage, conducted while she was on her deathbed,
1 CONT was considered non-canonical.
1 CONT
1 CONT Contents [hide]
