1 CONT MANFREDO [I] "Lancia", son of GUGLIELMO Marchese di Busca & his wife ---
1 CONT (-after 30 Aug 1187). Marchese di Busca. A charter dated 1183 records that
1 CONT "Marchese [Manfredo II di Saluzzo]" sold "la villa e castello di Dogliani" to
1 CONT "Manfredo Marchese di Busca, figliuolo d´un Guglielmo quondam Marchese…e
1 CONT Berengario suo fratello"[793]. "Dompnus Manfredus marchio de Busca, quondam
1 CONT Willelmi marchionis…et Bellingerii fratris sui" sold Dogliani to Manfredo II
1 CONT Marchese di Saluzzo by charter dated 30 Aug 1187[794]. His descendants adopted
1 CONT the name Lancia. m ---. The name of Manfredo's wife is not known. Manfredo [I]
1 CONT & his wife had one child:
1 CONT *1. MANFREDO [II] (-[1214/15]). ... m BIANCA Maletta, daughter of GUGLIELMO Maletta & his wife --- (-after [1214/15]). ... Manfredo [II] & his wife had eight children:
1 CONT **a)
1 CONT **b)
1 CONT **c) **BIANCA Lancia ([1205/12][804]-[1233/34])**. The Thomas Tusci Gesta
1 CONT Imperatorum et Pontificum refers to the mother of "Manfredus" as "sorore
1 CONT marchionis Lancee…filia domne Blanca"[805]. The Historia Sicula of Bartolomeo
1 CONT di Neocastro names "domina Blanca…de Lancea de Lombardia" as the fifth wife of
1 CONT "dominus Fridericus secundus…Romanorum…imperator"[806]. The Historia
1 CONT Manuscrita Mediolanensi records that Emperor Friedrich II married "filiam
1 CONT Bonefacii Castellani" by whom he fathered "Regem Manfredum"[807]. A
1 CONT "confirmatio matrimonii in articulo mortis" in [1233/34] is recorded by
1 CONT Matthew of Paris, in the form of a declaration of her son Manfred[808]. The
1 CONT Cronica Fratris Salimbene de Adam refers to the mother of "Manfredus…filius
1 CONT Friderici" as "marchionis Lancee neptis", specifying that she married the
1 CONT Emperor "in obitu"[809]. Mistress ([1231/34]) of Emperor FRIEDRICH II, son of
1 CONT Emperor HEINRICH VI & his wife Constance of Sicily (Iesi, Ancona 26 Dec
1 CONT 1194-Castel Fiorentino near Lucera, Foggia, 13 Dec 1250, bur 25 Feb 1251
1 CONT Palermo Cathedral).
1 CONT **d) ...
1 CONT **h)
