0 @N00383@ NOTE geni:about_me
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * <https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gioeni>
1 CONT
1 CONT The Gioeni are a noble family living in ancient times in Catania. They are a
1 CONT princely family descended from the royal dynasty of Anjou, their forefather
1 CONT was a consanguineous Henry or Arrigo of Anjou.
1 CONT
1 CONT Prince Arrigo (Henrico) of Anjou who, being a relative of King Charles of
1 CONT Anjou, passed to Italy as champion of the same prince for the acquisition of
1 CONT the Kingdoms of Naples and Sicily, and according to Paradino killed Manfredo
1 CONT Svevo King of Sicily in battle, therefore he obtained from Charles for wife
1 CONT Beatrice, daughter of the dead Manfred with the dowry of the States of Fiume
1 CONT di Nisi, Calatabiano, Noara, and the Motta di Camastra, and he died in 1270
1 CONT
1 CONT Three of his sons: Ruberto, Manfredo and Luigi in the massacre of the Sicilian
1 CONT Vespers were saved in the city of Reggio di Calabria by Niccolò Palici and
1 CONT Buonafede Collura, Messinian knights, and then reintegrated into their States
1 CONT by King Pietro of Aragon. Because of the hatred they felt the Sicilian
1 CONT families for the Angevins changed the surname to Gioeni, and they also changed
1 CONT the blazon.The family settled in Sicily following the vespers, enjoyed
1 CONT nobility in Palermo and Catania and had the lordship of 16 fiefs, 4 ducats and
1 CONT 5 principalities.
1 CONT
1 CONT \------------
