1 CONT James first married, in 1221, Eleanor, daughter of Alfonso VIII of Castile and
1 CONT Leonora of England. Though he later had the marriage annulled, his one son by
1 CONT her was declared legitimate:
1 CONT
1 CONT 1\. Alfonso (1229–1260), married Constance of Montcada, Countess of Bigorre
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1235, James remarried to Yolanda, daughter of Andrew II of Hungary by his
1 CONT second wife Yolande de Courtenay. She bore him numerous children:
1 CONT
1 CONT 1\. Yolanda, also known as Violant, (1236–1301), married Alfonso X of Castile
1 CONT 2\. Constance (1239–1269), married Juan Manuel, Lord of Villena, son of
1 CONT Ferdinand III
1 CONT 3\. Peter (1240–1285), successor in Aragon, Catalonia, and Valencia
1 CONT 4\. James (1243–1311), successor in Balearics and Languedoc
1 CONT 5\. Ferdinand (1245–1250)
1 CONT 6\. Sancha (1246–1251)
1 CONT 7\. Isabella (1247–1271), married Philip III of France
1 CONT 8\. Mary (1248–1267), nun
1 CONT 9\. Sancho, Archbishop of Toledo (1250–1279)
1 CONT 10\. Eleanor (born 1251, died young)
1 CONT
1 CONT James married thirdly Teresa Gil de Vidaure, but only by a private document,
1 CONT and left her when she developed leprosy.
