1 CONT Like his grandfather, ascended to the crown at the age of five. It was run by
1 CONT a regency until he came of age; and his uncle Sanc, Count of Provence,
1 CONT managed the finances and paid off his father's debts. He later became known
1 CONT for leading military campaigns that captured Majorca and the other Balearic
1 CONT islands, as well as Valencia, from the Moors.
1 CONT He was placed under regency at 5 years old of his great-uncle Count Sancho of
1 CONT Roussillin (in Aragon, now in France) until 1218 and began to govern on his
1 CONT own in 1227. He extended his kingdom by conquest and by marrying a daughter
1 CONT of Alfonso VIII of Castile. By his 2nd wife, he had many children, but made
1 CONT his eldest son, Peter, the principal heir. He helped his son-in-law, Alfonso
1 CONT X of Castile, to suppress the Moors. James was a stout, strong, handsome man
1 CONT and was criticized for his many love affairs.
1 CONT Like his grandfather, ascended to the crown at the age of five. It was run by
1 CONT a regency until he came of age; and his uncle Sanc, Count of Provence,
1 CONT managed the finances and paid off his father's debts. He later became known
1 CONT for leading military campaigns that captured Majorca and the other Balearic
1 CONT islands, as well as Valencia, from the Moors.
