0 @N00428@ NOTE (Beatrix Hohenstaufen di Sicilia)
0 @N00429@ NOTE geni:about_me
1 CONT
1 CONT -<https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beatrice_di_Sicilia>
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------
1 CONT
1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/SICILY.htm#Beatricedied1307>
1 CONT
1 CONT 2\. BEATRICE of Sicily (-[1307/08]). The Historia Sicula of Bartolomeo di
1 CONT Neocastro names "Beatrix" as the child of "Manfredum" and his second wife
1 CONT "Helenam filiam despoti regis Thessalie"[685]. After her capture with her
1 CONT mother at Trani following her father's death, she was imprisoned at the Castel
1 CONT dell'Uovo in Naples from 1271. The Chronicle of Ramon Muntaner records that
1 CONT "la fille du roi Mainfroi, sœur de la reine d´Arragon" was freed from "le
1 CONT château de l´Hou" by "Roger de Lauria", dated to 1284[686]. The contract of
1 CONT marriage between "Manfredo figlio primogenito del Marchese Tomaso di Saluzzo"
1 CONT and "Beatrice figlia del fù Re Manfredo, sorella della Regina Costanza
1 CONT d'Aragona e Sicilia" is dated 3 Jul 1286 and specifies the consent of
1 CONT "Marchese Tomaso di Saluzzo e Marchesa Alosia padre e madre di detto
1 CONT Manfredo"[687]. "Aloisia comitissa Salutiarum uxor Thomæ I marchionis
1 CONT Salutiarum" consented to donations by "eundem marchionem eorum filio
1 CONT Mainfredo" on the occasion of the latter´s marriage to "Beatrice filia quondam
1 CONT Mainfredi regis Siciliæ" by charter dated 1286[688].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** (1287) as his first wife, MANFREDO di Saluzzo, son of TOMMASO I Marchese
1 CONT di Saluzzo & his wife Luigia di Ceva ([1262]-Cortemiglia 16 Sep 1340). He
1 CONT succeeded his father in 1296 as MANFREDO IV Marchese di Saluzzo.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT \---------
