1 CONT b) RICCARDO di Chiaromonte (-executed Bari Oct 1139). "Albereda Colubrari
1 CONT Pollicorique domina" donated the church of San Nicola Peratico to Cava, for
1 CONT the souls of "Roberti Guiscardi ducis…bone memorie viri, Dominique Boamundi,
1 CONT nec non Rogerii de Pomareda…mei quondam viri, Dominique Ugonis
1 CONT Clarimontis…dominique Alexandri Clarimontis suique fratris domini Riccardi
1 CONT meorum…nepotum", by charter dated Jul 1122[20]. "Alexandro de Claromonte et
1 CONT Riccardo fratre meo" confirmed the donation of the church of Santa Maria di
1 CONT Scanzana to the monastery of San Anastasio di Carbone by "beatæ memoriæ
1 CONT Riccardi Sinescalci et dominæ Alberedæ amitæ nostræ et Petri Boiti et
1 CONT clarissimi dynastæ domini Boamundi", by charter dated Sep 1125, witnessed by
1 CONT "Hugo filius Raneri et Comestabulus, Hugo filius Ascintini de
1 CONT Claromonte…"[21]. The Chronicle of Romualdo Guarna records that
1 CONT "Goffredus…domini Alexandri comitis filius et Riccardus Clarimontis dominus"
1 CONT defended Brindisi in 1133 against King Roger who had returned from Sicily in
1 CONT May 1133 to recapture the citadel[22]. The Romoaldi Annales record that
1 CONT "Riccardus…de Claromonte" was killed at Bari, dated to Oct 1139, and
1 CONT "Alexander…frater eius" retreated "in Romaniam"[23].
