1 CONT
1 CONT GALEOTTO (-beheaded Naples, Piazza del Mercato 29 Oct 1268). Conte di Atti.
1 CONT The Alberti Milioli Notarii Regini Liber de Temporibus records the capture in
1 CONT 1268 of "Galvagno Lancia" and his death in Rome with his two sons[838].
1 CONT Galvano was beheaded with Konradin von Hohenstaufen ex-King of Sicily, Duke of
1 CONT Swabia.
1 CONT
