1 CONT underpretence of religious zeal. A favourer of the troubadours, he
1 CONT combinedgreat personal valour with the most lax morality. He was killed at
1 CONT thebattle of Muret (Sept. 12, 1213). [Encyclopædia Britannica, 1961 ed.,Vol.
1 CONT 17, p. 639, PETER II]; "el Catolico"
1 CONT
1 CONT "Pedro took a ... measure of precaution which aroused muchdissatisfaction
1 CONT among his subjects; he acknowledged the feudalsupremacy of the Papacy and was
1 CONT crowned at Rome by Innocent III in1204, undertaking to defend the Catholic
1 CONT faith, to respect theprivileges and immunities of the Church and to fight
1 CONT against heresy;he also promised that his kingdom should pay an annual tribute
1 CONT to thePapacy as a feudal vassal, in return for which the Pope and
1 CONT hissuccessors were to defend Pedro and his subjects with their
1 CONT apostolicauthority. Pedro received or assumed the title of Católico, but
1 CONT hisaction was greeted with unanimous disfavour by both his Aragonese
1 CONT andCatalan subjects, who declined to ratify it."
1 CONT
1 CONT <http://libro.uca.edu/chaytor/achistory.htm> Chapter 4
1 CONT
1 CONT "A History of Aragon and Catalonia" ; H. J. Chaytor
