1 CONT When he married Mary, Lady of Montpellier, the Angonese kingdom extended into
1 CONT southern France. When he went to support his brother-in-law Raymond VI of
1 CONT Toulouse against the crusader Simon de Montfort in Languedoc, he was killed
1 CONT in the Battle of Muret. He was succeeded by his son, James I.
1 CONT Led into ruinous alliance with Castile at the urging of his mother, his
1 CONT borrowings to cover various military adventures left his realm in dire
1 CONT financial straights. He was killed in a battle fighting French Knights led
1 CONT by the first Baron Simon de Montford (who earlier had been an ally).
