1 CONT Andreas II Arpád, King of Hungary (1)
1 CONT
1 CONT M, #104649, b. 1176, d. 7 March 1235
1 CONT
1 CONT Last Edited=19 Nov 2009
1 CONT
1 CONT Andreas II Arpád, King of Hungary was born in 1176. (3) He was the son of Béla
1 CONT III Arpád, King of Hungary and Agnes de Châtillon. (2) He married, secondly,
1 CONT Yolande de Courtney, daughter of Peter de Courtenay, Emperor of Constantinople
1 CONT and Yolande de Hainaut, before 29 January 1216. (4) He married, thirdly,
1 CONT Beatrice d'Este, daughter of Aldobrandino I, Marchese d'Este, in 1234. (3) He
1 CONT married, fourthly, Gertrud of Meran, daughter of Berthold II of Meran , Duke
1 CONT of Meran. (3)
1 CONT
1 CONT He died on 7 March 1235.
1 CONT
1 CONT Andreas II Arpád, King of Hungary gained the title of King Andreas II of
1 CONT Hungary in 1205. (2)
1 CONT
1 CONT Child of Andreas II Arpád, King of Hungary and Yolande de Courtney
