1 CONT Andrew II the Jerosolimitan (Hungarian: Jeruzsálemi II András/Endre, Croatian:
1 CONT Andrija II. Arpadovic Slovak: Ondrej, Serbian: Андрија II) (c. 1177 – 21
1 CONT September 1235), King of Hungary[1](1205-1235). He was the younger son of King
1 CONT Béla III of Hungary, who invested him with the government of the Principality
1 CONT of Halych.
