1 CONT ES 11:155;PED OF AUGUSTINE H. AYERS
1 CONT OR "ANDREW"; "OF JERUSALEM"; KING OF THE MAGYARS/HUNGARY 1205-1235; LEADER OF
1 CONT THE 5TH CRUSADE (1218-1221)
1 CONT He deposed his brother Imre's son Ladislas II in 1205. He ruined his country's
1 CONT finances through weakness and was forced by his nobles to sign "The Golden
1 CONT Bull" of 1222 (Hungary's Magna Carta) which gave all lords the right to
1 CONT disallow any royal act.
