1 CONT [<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/LATIN%20EMPERORS.htm#PierreIEmpdied1219B>
1 CONT MedLands]
1 CONT
1 CONT <http://genealogy.euweb.cz/capet/capet7.html>
1 CONT
1 CONT Prince Pierre I de France, sn de Courtenay, de Tanlay, de Champignelles, etc,
1 CONT *1126, +Palestine 1179/10.4.1183 !dwid!; m.1150/55 Elizabeth de Joinville,
1 CONT Dame de Courtenay (*Courtenay 1127, +after 14.9.1205) dau.of Renaud de
1 CONT Courtenay; they had issue:
1 CONT
1 CONT   * A1. Cte Pierre II de Courtenay 1193, Cte de Nevers, d'Auxerre et de Tonnerre 1184, Emperor of Constantinople (1216-19), Marquis de Namur, *1155, +Epirus after VI.1219; By his second marriage, he was called upon in 1217 to succeed to the Latin E
1 CONC mpire of the Orient, created following the capture of Constantinople in the course of the Fourth Crusade. But on the way to his Empire, he was victim of a Greek ambush. Baudouin tried to engage the fief of Courtenay to Villehardouin, but King Louis
1 CONC  IX objected. However, his son Philippe was able to engage to the Venetians. Later, through marriage, Courtenay was reunited with the Crown, after a possession by the King of Castile; 1m: 1184 Cts Agnes de Nevers, d'Auxerre et de Tonnerre (*1170 +1
1 CONC 192) dau.of Cte Guy I de Nevers and Mathilde de Bourgogne; 2m: Soissons 1.7.1193 Mgvne Yolande of Namur (*1175 +1219) dau.of Ct Baldwin V of Flanders and Hainaut
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B1. [1m.] Mahaut de Courtenay, Cts de Nevers, d'Auxerre et de Tonnerre, *1188, +Abbaye de Fontevrault 12.10.1257, bur there; 1m: 1199 (div 1213) Hervé IV, Seigneur de Donzy; 2m: 1226 Guigues IV d'Albon, Cte de Forez (+1241)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B2. [2m.] Philippe de Courtenay, Margrave of Namur (1217-26), *1195, +k.a. St.Flour-en-Auvergne 1226, bur Abbaye de Vaucelles, Cambrai
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B3. [2m.] Pierre de Courtenay, a priest, *1196, living 1212
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B4. [2m.] Robert I de Courtenay, Emperor of Constantinople (1221-28), *1201, +Morea/Morée, Loir-et-Cher, France I.1228; m.1228 a dau.of Baudoin de Neufville
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B5. [2m.] Henri de Courtenay, Mgve of Namur (1226-29), *1206, +1229
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B6. [2m.] Baldwin de Courtenay, Emperor of Constantinople (1237-61) =Baldwin II, *Constantinople 1218, +Naples 1273, bur Barletta; m.Perugia 1229/1234 Marie de Brienne (+after 5.5.1275)
1 CONT
1 CONT       * ..
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B7. [2m.] Marguerite, Dame de Chateauneuf-sur-Cher, Mgvne of Namur (1229-37), *1194, +17.7.1270, bur Marienthal; 1m: ca 1210 Raoul I de Lusignan, Seigneur d'Issoudun (+1216); 2m: 1216 Gf Heinrich I von Vianden (+1252)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B8. [2m.] Sibylle, a nun, *1197, +Abbey de Fontevrault V.1210
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B9. [2m.] Elizabeth, *1199, +after 1269; 1m: before 1219 Cte Gaucher de Bar-sur-Seine (+1219); 2m: 1220 Eudes I de Bourgogne, sn de Montagu (*1196 +1243/7)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B10. [2m.] **Yolande de Courtenay, *ca 1194, 1200, +1233, bur Egrecz Abbey** ; m.1215 King András II of Hungary (*1176 +21.9.1235)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B11. [2m.] Agnés, *1202, +after 1247; m.1217 Geoffroy II de Villehardouin, Pr of Achaia (+1246), son of Geoffroy de Villehardouin and Elisabeth de Troyes
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B12. [2m.] Marie, *1204, +Nicea IX.1222; m.1219 Emperor Theodoros I of Nicaea (+1222)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B13. [2m.] Eléonore de Courtenay, *1208, +1230, bur Abbaye de St.Antoine-des-Champs, Paris; m.before 1220 Philippe I de Montfort-l'Amaury, sn de Castres-en-Albegeois (+17.3.1270)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B14. [2m.] Constance, a nun at Fontevrault, *1210, +Abbaye de Fontevrault after 1215, bur there
1 CONT
1 CONT   * ...
1 CONT
1 CONT Yolande de Courtney married Andreas II Arpád, King of Hungary, son of Béla III
1 CONT Arpád, King of Hungary and Agnes de Châtillon, before 29 January 1216.1 She
1 CONT died in 1233.2
1 CONT She was the daughter of Peter de Courtenay, Emperor of Constantinople and
1 CONT Yolande de Hainaut.1,2 Child of Yolande de Courtney and Andreas II Arpád, King
1 CONT of Hungary
1 CONT
1 CONT Yolante Arpád+2 d. c Oct 1251
