1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT Yolanda de Courtenay
1 CONT
1 CONT Yolanda de Courtenay (1197 - June 1233) Queen Consort of Hungary, Second wife
1 CONT of Andrew II of Hungary.
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit] Biography
1 CONT
1 CONT Yolanda is registered under different versions of his name in contemporary
1 CONT documents, including:Yoles, Hyolenz, Jole, Hyole, Jolans, among others
1 CONT Violanta". He was born in Constantinople in Latin Empire, As the daughter of
1 CONT Emperor Peter II of Courtenay and his consort Empress Yolanda of Flanders.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1215 was taken as a wife widowed by King Andrew II of Hungary, after his
1 CONT first wife Gertrude had been killed in Merani 1213. With this second marriage,
1 CONT Andrew II wanted to approach the Latin Empire, heir of the Byzantine Empire
1 CONT momentary crisis, strengthening political relations with the emperor-family,
1 CONT however this failed. Yolanda had a daughter with Andrés II Violante of Hungary
1 CONT in 1216 (Who later married the king Jaime I of Aragon)
1 CONT
1 CONT Yolanda was very different from its predecessor Gertrudis. The new queen
1 CONT consort was sweet-tempered and serene, away from politics as possible, just
1 CONT the opposite of Gertrude. Yolanda finished the first church in Arad carrying
1 CONT about 80 years under construction, and 1224 The Temple was sanctified.
1 CONT
1 CONT Yolanda died in June 1233 and was buried in the cloister of the Cistercian
1 CONT order Built in the ?**City Eger**.
1 CONT
1 CONT <http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yolanda_de_Courtenay>
1 CONT
1 CONT (Translation from Spanish)
