0 @N00499@ NOTE (Maria de Montpellier reine d'Aragon)
0 @N00500@ NOTE geni:about_me Marie of Montpellier (adapted from Occitan: Maria de
1 CONT Montpelhièr) (1182 – 18 April 1213) was the daughter of William VIII of
1 CONT Montpellier and Eudokia Komnene. A condition of the marriage was that the
1 CONT firstborn child, boy or girl, would succeed to the lordship of Montpellier on
1 CONT William's death.
1 CONT
1 CONT Marie married Barral of Marseille in 1192 or shortly before, but was widowed
1 CONT in that year. Her second marriage, in 1197, was to Bernard IV of Comminges,
1 CONT and her father now insisted on her giving up her right to inherit Montpellier.
1 CONT Marie had two daughters by Bernard, Mathilde and Petronille. The marriage was,
1 CONT however, notoriously polygamous, Bernard having two other living wives. It was
1 CONT annulled (some say on Marie's insistence, some say on that of Peter II of
1 CONT Aragon) and the annulment meant that she was once more heir to Montpellier.
1 CONT
1 CONT William had died in 1202. Marie's half-brother, William's son by Agnes of
1 CONT Castile, William, had taken control of the city, but Marie asserted her right
1 CONT to it. On 15 June 1204 she married Peter II and was recognised as Lady of
1 CONT Montpellier. Her son by Peter, James, the future James the Conqueror, was born
1 CONT on 1 February 1208. Peter immediately attempted to divorce her, hoping both to
1 CONT marry Maria of Montferrat, Queen of Jerusalem, and to claim Montpellier for
1 CONT himself. Marie's last years were spent in combating these political and
1 CONT matrimonial manoeuvres. Pope Innocent III finally decided in her favour,
1 CONT refusing to permit the divorce. Both Marie and Peter died in 1213; James
1 CONT inherited Aragon and Montpellier.
1 CONT
1 CONT <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marie_of_Montpellier>
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT
1 CONT J. M. Lacarra, L. Gonzalez Anton, 'Les testaments de la reine Marie de
1 CONT Montpellier' in Annales du Midi vol. 90 (1978) pp. 105-120.
1 CONT
1 CONT M. Switten, 'Marie de Montpellier: la femme et le pouvoir en Occitanie au
1 CONT douzième siècle' in Actes du Premier Congrès International de l'Association
1 CONT d'Etudes Occitanes ed. P. T. Ricketts (London: Westfield College, 1987) pp.
1 CONT 485-491.
1 CONT
1 CONT K. Varzos, I genealogia ton Komninon (Thessalonica, 1984) vol. 2 pp. 346-359.
1 CONT
