1 CONT HEIRESS OF SICILY
1 CONT She had appointed Pope Innocent III as her son's guardian as well as her son's
1 CONT regent of the kingdom of Sicily, which was already under papal suzerainty.
1 CONT Her marriage to a Hohenstaufen gave the German dynasty a claim to the throne
1 CONT of Sicily, but her political skill preserved the throne for her son,
1 CONT Frederick II, crowned king in April 1198. On the death of her nephew, Tancred
1 CONT II (1189), Constance claimed the crown of Sicily, but the Sicilians supported
1 CONT Tancred of Lecce. But he died in 1194, allowing her to take the throne.
1 CONT (Research):Constance Constance, 1154-98, Holy Roman empress, wife of Holy
1 CONT Roman Emperor Henry VI; daughter of King Roger II of Sicily. She was named
1 CONT heiress of Sicily by her nephew King William II. On his death, however (1189),
1 CONT the Sicilian nobles, wishing to prevent German rule in Sicily, chose
1 CONT Constance's nephew Tancred of Lecce as William's successor. Henry VI conducted
1 CONT an unsuccessful campaign (1191) against Tancred during which Constance was
1 CONT captured but soon released. After Tancred's death (1194) Henry was crowned
1 CONT king of Sicily. When he died (1197) all of Italy revolted against German rule.
1 CONT In order to save the throne of Sicily for her infant son Frederick (later Holy
1 CONT Roman emperor as Frederick II), Constance renounced the German kingship for
1 CONT Frederick and had him crowned (1198) king of Sicily. She was regent for her
1 CONT son; before her death she named Pope Innocent III his guardian.
1 CONT She had appointed Pope Innocent III as her son's guardian as well as her son's
1 CONT regent of the kingdom of Sicily, which was already under papal suzerainty.
1 CONT Her marriage to a Hohenstaufen gave the German dynasty a claim to the throne
1 CONT of Sicily, but her political skill preserved the throne for her son,
1 CONT Frederick II, crowned king in April 1198. On the death of her nephew, Tancred
1 CONT II (1189), Constance claimed the crown of Sicily, but the Sicilians supported
1 CONT Tancred of Lecce. But he died in 1194, allowing her to take the throne.
1 CONT She had appointed Pope Innocent III as her son's guardian as well as her son's
1 CONT regent of the kingdom of Sicily, which was already under papal suzerainty.
