1 CONT [edit] Marriage and Issue
1 CONT
1 CONT On 23 May 1200, at the age of twelve, Louis married Blanche of Castile (4
1 CONT March 1188 – 26 November 1252).
1 CONT
1 CONT Blanche (1205–1206).
1 CONT
1 CONT Agnes (b. and d. 1207).
1 CONT
1 CONT Philippe (9 September 1209 – July 1218), married (or only betrothed) in 1217
1 CONT to Agnes of Donzy.
1 CONT
1 CONT Alphonse (b. and d. Lorrez-le-Bocage, 23 January 1213).
1 CONT
1 CONT John (b. and d. Lorrez-le-Bocage, 23 January 1213), twin of Alphonse.
1 CONT
1 CONT Louis IX (Poissy, 25 April 1214 – 25 August 1270, Tunis), King of France as
1 CONT successor to his father.
1 CONT
1 CONT Robert (25 September 1216 – 9 February 1250, killed in Battle of Al Mansurah,
1 CONT Egypt)
1 CONT
1 CONT Philippe (2 January 1218–1220).
1 CONT
1 CONT John Tristan (21 July 1219–1232), Count of Anjou and Maine.
1 CONT
1 CONT Alphonse (Poissy, 11 November 1220 – 21 August 1271, Corneto), Count of Poitou
1 CONT and Auvergne, and by marriage, of Toulouse.
1 CONT
1 CONT Philippe Dagobert (20 February 1222–1232).
1 CONT
1 CONT Isabel (14 April 1225 – 23 February 1269).
1 CONT
1 CONT Charles Etienne (21 March 1226 – 7 January 1285), Count of Anjou and Maine, by
1 CONT marriage Count of Provence and Folcalquier, and King of Sicily.
