1 CONT [FAVthomas.FTW]
1 CONT
1 CONT Byname Louis The Lion, or The Lion-heart, French Louis Le Lion, orLouis Coeur-
1 CONT de-lion Capetian king of France from 1223 who spent most ofhis short reign
1 CONT establishing royal power in Poitou and Languedoc.
1 CONT On May 23, 1200, Louis married Blanche de Castile, daughter of AlfonsoVIII de
1 CONT Castile, who effectively acted as regent after Louis's death. In1212 Louis
1 CONT seized Saint-Omer and Aire to prevent a powerful Flanders frombeing on the
1 CONT flank of his county of Artois. In 1216, after the baronsrebelling against King
1 CONT John of England had offered the English throne toLouis in return for his aid,
1 CONT Louis went to England to aid the rebels.Initially he was successful, but
1 CONT eventually he was defeated at sea andsuffered defections. In 1217, when peace
1 CONT was concluded at Kingston, Louiswas secretly paid 10,000 marks. In 1224, now
1 CONT king, he seized Poitou and,in 1226, he launched a successful crusade against
1 CONT the Albigensianheretics, capturing the major fortress of Avignon before
1 CONT returning towardParis because of illness.
1 CONT Louis was the first Capetian to grant appanages on a large scale andto have a
1 CONT reversion clause that made alienation of royal property moredifficult. Louis
1 CONT also developed other particular rights for the kingship,such as the concept
1 CONT that fealty was sworn not only to the individual kingbut also to the kingship.
1 CONT His eldest son, Louis IX (afterward St. Louis),peacefully succeeded him while
1 CONT his other sons received appanages.
1 CONT
