1 CONT
1 CONT He was also Count of Artois from 1190, inheriting the county from his mother.
1 CONT
1 CONT On 1 November 1223, he issued an ordinance that prohibited his officials from
1 CONT recording debts owed to Jews, thus reversing the policies set by his father
1 CONT Philip II Augustus. Usury (lending money withinterest) was illegal for
1 CONT Christians to practice. According to Church law it was seen as a vice in which
1 CONT people profited from others' misfortune (like gambling), and was punishable by
1 CONT excommunication,a severe punishment. However since Jews were not Christian,
1 CONT they could not be excommunicated, and thus fell in to a legal gray area which
1 CONT secular rulers would sometimes exploit by allowing (or requesting) Jews to
1 CONT provide usury services, often for personal gain to the secular ruler, and to
1 CONT the discontent of the Church. Louis VIII's prohibition was one attempt at
1 CONT resolving this legal problem whichwas a constant source of friction in Church
1 CONT and State courts.
