1 CONT
1 CONT On June 14 he captured Winchester and soon conquered over half of the English
1 CONT kingdom. Since other English Kings such as Edward V (1483) an d Edward VIII
1 CONT (1936) were not crowned but only proclaimed, there is a good case for
1 CONT including Louis VIII in the list of Kings of England. Af ter a year and a half
1 CONT of war, most of the rebellious barons had defect ed and so Louis had to give
1 CONT up his claim to be the King of England bys igning the Treaty of Lambeth in
1 CONT 1217. Coronation of Louis VIII and Bl anche of Castile at Reims in 1223; a
1 CONT miniature from the Grandes Chroni ques de France, painted in the 1450s, kept
1 CONT at the National Library of France. Louis VIII succeeded his father on July 14,
