1 CONT   * <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramon_Berenguer_IV,_Count_of_Provence> _[23 languages]_
1 CONT
1 CONT **Ramon Berenguer V** (French: _Raimond-Bérenger_ ; 1198 – 19 August 1245) was
1 CONT a member of the House of Barcelona who ruled as count of Provence and
1 CONT Forcalquier. He was the first count of Provence to live in the county in more
1 CONT than one hundred years. During the minority of a previous count, the regency
1 CONT was exercised by Ramon Berenguer IV de Barcelona, who is sometimes counted
1 CONT among the counts of Provence. .. ...
1 CONT
1 CONT \-------
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * <http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/PROVENCE.htm#RaymondBerengerIVdied1245>
1 CONT
1 CONT **RAYMOND BERENGER de Provence** , son of ALPHONSE II Comte de Provence
1 CONT [Aragon-Barcelona] & his wife Gersende de Sabran Ctss de Forcalquier
1 CONT ([1198]-Aix 19 Aug 1245, bur Aix-en-Provence, église de Saint Jean de
1 CONT Jérusalem). “Garsendis uxor quondam Ildefonsi comitis Provinciæ” donated her
1 CONT rights “in comitatu Forcalqueriensi”, granted by “Guillelmo quondam comite
1 CONT Forcalqueriensi avo meo”, to “Raymundo Berengario filio meo” with “filiæ meæ
1 CONT sororis tuæ Garsendis” as substitute should he die, with the consent of “patre
1 CONT meo Raines de Castelar”, by charter dated 30 Nov 1209[422]. He succeeded his
1 CONT father in 1209 as RAYMOND BERENGER IV Comte de Provence et de Forcalquier.
1 CONT Under his testament dated 20 Jun 1238, he designated his fourth daughter as
1 CONT his heir[423]. The testament of “R. Berengarius…comes et marchio Provincie et
1 CONT comes Forcalquerii”, dated 20 Jun 1238, names “Margaritam filiam
1 CONT nostrum…reginam Francie…Elionors filiam nostrum…reginam Anglie…Sanciam filiam
1 CONT nostram” and appoints “Beatricem filiam nostrum heredem generalem”[424]. The
1 CONT Annales Sancti Victoris Massilienses record the death "1245 XIV Kal Sep" of
1 CONT "Raimundus Berengarius comes Provincie" at Aix[425]. The Obituaire of
1 CONT Forcalquier St Mary records the death "XIV Kal Sep" of "Raymundus
1 CONT Berengarii…comes Provincie et Forcalquerii"[426]. The Thalamus de Montpellier
1 CONT records the death Aug 1244 of "R. Berenguier coms de Proensa" at Aix[427].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** (Betrothed 5 Jun 1219, Dec 1220) BEATRIX de Savoie, daughter of THOMAS I
1 CONT Comte de Savoie & his wife Marguerite [Beatrix] de Genève ([1205][428]-Dec
1 CONT 1266 or 4 Jan 1267). .. ... ....
1 CONT
1 CONT Comte Raymond Bérenger IV & his wife had five children:
1 CONT # MARGUERITE de Provence (St Maime near Forcalquier Spring 1221-Paris, Abbaye
1 CONT de St Marcel 21 Dec 1295, bur église de l'Abbaye royale de Saint-Denis). ..
1 CONT ...
1 CONT _m_ (Cathedral of St Etienne, Sens, Yonne 27 May 1234) LOUIS IX King of
1 CONT France, ..
1 CONT # ELEONORE de Provence (Aix-en-Provence [1223]-Amesbury Abbey, Wiltshire 24/25
1 CONT Jun 1291, bur Amesbury Abbey).
1 CONT _m_ (Betrothed 22 Jun 1235, Canterbury 14 Jan 1236) HENRY III King of England,
1 CONT ..
1 CONT # SANCHA de Provence (Aix-en-Provence [1225]-Berkhamstead Castle,
1 CONT Buckinghamshire 5 or 9 Nov 1261, bur Hayles Abbey, Gloucestershire).
1 CONT _Betrothed_ (contract before Jun 1240, _annulled_ Jun 1240) to GUIGUES Dauphin
1 CONT de Viennois Comte d'Albon ..
1 CONT _Betrothed_ (Aug 1241) to RAYMOND VII Comte de Toulouse, ..
1 CONT _m_ (Contract 17 Jul 1242, Westminster 22 Nov 1243) as his second wife,
1 CONT RICHARD Earl of Cornwall, son of JOHN King of England ..
1 CONT # RAYMOND de Provence (-young).
1 CONT # BEATRICE de Provence ([1232/34]-Naples 23 Sep 1267, bur Naples, Cathedral of
1 CONT San Gennaro, transferred 1277 to Aix-en-Provence, Church of St Jean de
1 CONT Jerusalem). .. ... ....
1 CONT _m_ (Aix-en-Provence 31 Jan 1246) as his first wife, CHARLES de France Comte
1 CONT d'Anjou et de Maine, .. CHARLES I King of Sicily ..
