1 CONT After his father's death in 1209, Ramón Berenguer IV, Count of Provence and
1 CONT Forcalquier, was imprisoned in the castle of Monzón, in Aragon, until he was
1 CONT able to escape in 1219 and claim his inheritance. He was a powerful and
1 CONT energetic ruler who added Forcalquier to his domain.
1 CONT
1 CONT Giovanni Villani in his Nuova Cronica had this to say about Raymond: "Count
1 CONT Raymond was a lord of gentle lineage, and kin to them of the house of Aragon,
1 CONT and to the family of the count of Toulouse. By inheritance Provence, this side
1 CONT of the Rhone, was his; a wise and courteous lord was he, and of noble state
1 CONT and virtuous, and in his time did honorable deeds, and to his court came all
1 CONT gentle persons of Provence and of France and of Catalonia, by reason of his
1 CONT courtesy and noble estate, and he made many Provençal coblas and canzoni of
1 CONT great worth."
1 CONT
