1 CONT
1 CONT Berenger was the last and most illustrious of the Royal Provençal Counts; and,
1 CONT even had he not been the sovereign of the land of song, his own verses would
1 CONT have entitled him to a distinguised rank among the Troubadour poets.
1 CONT By Ramon's time Provence had been at peace for two and a half centuries. There
1 CONT were few lands that had enjoyed peace and prosperity with so little
1 CONT interruption. Since the end of the tenth century Provence had grown more in
1 CONT population and wealth than any other part of Europe.
1 CONT Few men in history have been more successful in finding powerful and
1 CONT influential mates for their daughters than Ramon. His four daughters married
1 CONT two sets of brothers - all of them kings! Margaret married King Louis IX of
1 CONT France; ELEANOR married KING HENRY III OF ENGLAND; Sanchia married HENRY's
1 CONT brother, Richard of Cornwall, who was recognized for a time as the German
1 CONT Emporer; and Beatrice, the youngest and his appointed heir, married Louis'
1 CONT brother, Charles of Anjou, who at one time or another held
1 CONT the titles King of Sicily and King of Jerusalem and was briefly master of most
1 CONT of Italy and Greece. He was almost able to make an independent stateof
1 CONT Burgundy.
