1 CONT Sicilianu ([<http://scn.wikipedia.org/wiki/Custanza_d%27Aragona> SCN]):
1 CONT **Custanza d'Aragona** , **Custanza II di Sicilia** o **Custanza di
1 CONT Hohenstaufen** (Catania, 1249 – Barcillona, 1302) fu na suvrana siciliana;
1 CONT principessa sveva fu riggina d'Aragona (1262-1285) e doppu lu ntirventu
1 CONT aragunisi duranti li Vespri siciliani (1282) riggina di Sicilia nzinu ô 1285.
1 CONT
1 CONT Català ([<http://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constan%C3%A7a_de_Sic%C3%ADlia> CA]):
1 CONT **Constança de Sicília** (Catània, Sicília 1247 - Barcelona, 1302) fou reina
1 CONT consort d'Aragó i de València i comtessa de Barcelona (1276-1285), i reina de
1 CONT Sicília (1282-1302). Proclamada beata per l'Església Catòlica.
1 CONT
1 CONT Español ([<http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constanza_II_de_Sicilia> ES]):
1 CONT **Constanza de Sicilia** o **Constanza de Suabia** (Sicilia, 1247 - Barcelona,
1 CONT 1302), reina consorte de Aragón (1276-1302) y reina de Sicilia (1282-1302).
1 CONT
1 CONT Português ([<http://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constan%C3%A7a_de_Hohenstaufen>
1 CONT PT]): **Constança de Hohenstaufen** (Catania, Sicília 1249-Barcelona 9 de
1 CONT Abril de 1302) foi rainha consorte de Aragão e Valência de 1275 e rainha da
1 CONT Sicília de 1247 até à sua morte. Está proclamada beata pela Igreja Católica.
1 CONT
1 CONT English ([<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constance_of_Sicily,_Queen_of_Aragon>
1 CONT EN]): **Constantia** or **Constance** (1249 - 9 April 1302) was the Queen
1 CONT consort of Peter III of Aragon.
1 CONT
1 CONT \------------
1 CONT
1 CONT One of her [<https://www.geni.com/people/una-dama-di-compagnia-di-Costanza-di-
1 CONT Hohenstaufen/6000000173092341493> " lady-in-waiting "] originated the
1 CONT [<https://www.geni.com/people/Bartolomeo-Tagliavia-1-barone-di-
1 CONT Castelvetrano/6000000164296947933> Tagliavia family tree line].
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT HGCRP-Tomo I-pg. 175 -Tab. 17
1 CONT
1 CONT Constança de Hohenstaufen (1249-9 de Abril de 1302) foi princesa da Sicília e
1 CONT rainha de Aragão de 1275 até à sua morte.
1 CONT
1 CONT Era filha de Beatriz de Sabóia (1230-c.1259) e de Manfredo, rei da Sicília
1 CONT (1232 — 26 de Fevereiro de 1266). Era neta materna de Ana de Borgonha e do
1 CONT conde Amadeu IV de Sabóia e neta paterna da condessa Branca de Lancia e de
1 CONT Frederico II de Hohenstauffen, Imperador do Sacro Império Romano Germânico,
1 CONT rei da Sicília, sendo Constança por isso descendente da poderosa família
1 CONT Hohenstaufen que reinou no Sacro Império Romano Germânico e na Sicília durante
1 CONT a Idade Média.
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT Constantia of Sicily
1 CONT
1 CONT Constantia or Constance (1249 - 9 April 1302) was the Queen consort of Peter
1 CONT III of Aragon.
1 CONT
1 CONT She was the only daughter of Manfred of Sicily and his first wife Beatrice of
1 CONT Savoy. Her paternal grandparents were Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor and his
1 CONT mistress Bianca Lancia. Her maternal grandparents were Amadeus IV of Savoy and
1 CONT his first wife Anne of Burgundy.
1 CONT
1 CONT Anne was a daughter of Eudes III, Duke of Burgundy and his second wife Alice
1 CONT of Vergy.
1 CONT
1 CONT On 13 June 1262, Constantia married Prince Peter of Aragon, eldest son of
1 CONT James I of Aragon and his second wife Violant of Hungary.
1 CONT
1 CONT Manfred was killed in the Battle of Benevento (26 February 1266) while
1 CONT fighting against his rival Charles of Anjou, posthumous son of Louis VIII of
1 CONT France and Blanche of Castile. As his eldest daughter she could be considered
1 CONT his heiress but did not pursue her claim at this time.
1 CONT
1 CONT James I died on 27 July 1276 and Peter succeeded to the throne. Constance
1 CONT became his Queen consort. With the War of the Sicilian Vespers (1282 - 1302),
1 CONT at first Peter and then their sons claimed the throne of Sicily in her right.
1 CONT The War resulted in the partition of the Kingdom of Sicily to the "Kingdom of
1 CONT Trinacria" (the island of Sicily) under her descendants and the Kingdom of
1 CONT Naples under the descendants of Charles of Anjou.
1 CONT
1 CONT Peter III died on 2 November 1285 and Constantia remained a widow. She ended
1 CONT her days as a nun in Barcelona.
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT [http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-
1 CONT bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GRid=8062250](http://www.findagrave.com/cgi-
1 CONT bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GRid=8062250)
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT En mi nuevo libro LA SORPRENDENTE GENEALOGÍA DE MIS TATARABUELOS, encontrarán
1 CONT a este y muchos otros de sus ancestros con un resumen biográfico de cada uno.
1 CONT El libro está disponible en: amazon.com barnesandnoble.com palibrio.com. Les
1 CONT será de mucha utilidad y diversión. Ramón Rionda
1 CONT
1 CONT In my new book LA SORPRENDENTE GENEALOGÍA DE MIS TATARABUELOS, you will find
1 CONT this and many other of your ancestors, with a biography summary of each of
1 CONT them. The book is now available at: amazon.com barnesandnoble.com
1 CONT palibrio.com. Check it up, it’s worth it. Ramón Rionda
1 CONT WINKHAUS;KRAENTZLER,P. 24
1 CONT Constança de Hohenstaufen (1249-1302) foi princesa da Sicília e rainha de
1 CONT Aragão de 1275 até à sua morte.
1 CONT
1 CONT Era filha de Beatriz de Sabóia (1230-c.1259) e de Manfredo, rei da Sicília
1 CONT (1232 — 26 de Fevereiro de 1266). Era neta materna de Ana de Borgonha e do
1 CONT conde Amadeu IV de Sabóia e neta paterna da condessa Branca de Lancia e de
1 CONT Frederico II de Hohenstauffen, Imperador do Sacro Império Romano Germânico,
1 CONT rei da Sicília, sendo Constança por isso descendente da poderosa família
1 CONT Hohenstaufen que reinou no Sacro Império Romano Germânico e na Sicília durante
1 CONT a Idade Média.
1 CONT "OF SICILY"
1 CONT The daughter of Manfred, she was bethrothed to the infante Peter of Aragon in
1 CONT 1260\. This was a way of strengthening Manfred's position as King of Sicily as
1 CONT "protector of the Italian Ghibellines".
1 CONT The daughter of Manfred, she was bethrothed to the infante Peter of Aragon in
1 CONT 1260\. This was a way of strengthening Manfred's position as King of Sicily as
1 CONT "protector of the Italian Ghibellines".
