1 CONT just agreement with the imprisoned heir of Charles of Anjou; but the pope,
1 CONT disallowing this, ordered an offensive against Sicily in 1287, a disastrous
1 CONT affair for Honorious IV. When in 1291 her eldest son, Alfonso III "The
1 CONT Liberal", King of Aragon, died childless, it was Jaime, King of Sicily, who
1 CONT became the next King of Aragon. He remained king of both countries until 1296
1 CONT when Fadrique, Constance's third son, became King of Sicily and Jaime remained
1 CONT King of Aragon alone. Constance, having returned to Spain, died in Barcelona
1 CONT in 1301. Source: Leo van de Pas
1 CONT
1 CONT Constance of Sicily (1249-1301) Born 1249 Died 1301 Barcelona Married 13 June
1 CONT 1262 Montpellier Pedro III "the Great", King of Aragon 1276-1285, King of
1 CONT Sicily, son of Jaime I "the Conqueror", King of Aragon 1213-1276 and Violante
1 CONT of Hungary Born 1236 Died 11 November 1285 Villafranca de Penadres Buried
1 CONT Villafranca, Holy Cross It was to the annoyance of the pope when in 1262 her
1 CONT father arranged her engagement and marriage to Infant Pedro of Aragon, son and
1 CONT heir of King Jaime "The Conqueror". However, this also upset King Louis IX of
1 CONT France who then almost broke off his son's engagement to Pedro's sister. It
1 CONT was only after Jaime "The Conqueror" promised never to assist Manfredo,
1 CONT Constance's father, that the marriage proceeded. However, due to papal
1 CONT interference, Manfredo lost his crown and life in 1266. As long as Constance's
1 CONT father-in-law had been alive, nothing was done about Sicily; and now, even
1 CONT though she was Sicily's heiress, it remained in the hands of Charles of Anjou,
1 CONT a brother of King Louis IX of France. Her husband---who loved her dearly, and
1 CONT even some years before he became king---gave her in her own right the title of
1 CONT queen. When her father-in-law died in 1276 he had left the Balearic Islands
1 CONT and Roussillon to a younger son, Jaime, who, as well as calling himself King
1 CONT of Majorca, for three years refused to acknowledge Constance's husband as his
1 CONT suzerain. In 1279 the Moors of Andalusia tried to reconquer Murcia and it took
1 CONT till the end of that year before the southern border was secure. Further
1 CONT intrigues within the Iberian peninsula prevented King Pedro III of Aragon from
1 CONT pursuing his wife's rights in Sicily. In 1275 the elder son of King Alfonso X
1 CONT of Castile had died, leaving two young sons. Alfonso X decided to make his
1 CONT second son, Sancho, his heir to prevent a long minority for his grandson, the
1 CONT rightful heir. However, his widowed daughter-in-law, Blanche, a daughter of
1 CONT Louis IX of France, fled with her two sons to Pedro III of Aragon as she
1 CONT feared for her sons' lives. Pedro III of Aragon welcomed Blanche and her sons
1 CONT but kept them as hostages. Alfonso X of Castile soon regretted his decision as
1 CONT in 1281 the impatient Sancho rebelled against his father. However, in 1279 the
1 CONT plotting began in earnest with Emperor Michael of Constantinople and the
1 CONT Republic of Genoa, as these greatly feared that Charles of Anjou, the de-facto
1 CONT king of Sicily, might become too powerful. On 30 August 1282, the Aragonese,
1 CONT with King Pedro III at its head, disembarked at Trapani for Sicily, so that
1 CONT the local rebellion became a European war. On 2 October Pedro III made a
1 CONT triumphant entry into Messina. Nevertheless he acted most cautiously as one
1 CONT night a ragged old man, Vitalis dei Guidici who was once a devoted friend of
1 CONT King Manfredo, warned him of the inconstancy of the volatile Sicilian nobles.
1 CONT Pedro III maintained that he had come to make friends with the Sicilians and
1 CONT not to offend them with recriminations about the past. However, the very next
1 CONT day he was reminded of the warning when Lady Machalda, one of those mentioned
1 CONT by name by Vitalis dei Guidici, came and made it clear that she wanted to
1 CONT become his mistress. He escaped only by a lengthy discourse about his loyalty
1 CONT to his wife Constance, the rightful queen of Sicily. Lady Machalda, not a
1 CONT graceful loser, then induced her own husband to intrigue against Pedro III and
1 CONT Constance. In the early spring of 1283 when her husband sent for her,
1 CONT Constance left Aragon for Sicily and, with her children---Jaime, Fadrique and
1 CONT Yolanda---arrived on 16 April 1283. On 19 April it was announced that the
1 CONT Infant Jaime would be heir to Sicily as the elder son, Alfonso, would remain
1 CONT heir of Aragon. In the case of Jaime's minority, Constance would act as
1 CONT regent. Pedro III had to depart Sicily, leaving Constance in charge. Constance
1 CONT and her Italian-born ministers were careful to observe the rights of the
1 CONT Sicilians, but, soon short of money, she found it difficult to restrain the
1 CONT rapacious Aragonese soldiers. When Sicily was again attacked, it was only the
1 CONT brilliance of Admiral Roger of Lauria which saved it from an invasion. Soon
1 CONT the whole kingdom of Charles of Anjou was in turmoil and, with his having lost
1 CONT Sicily to Pedro III and Constance, riots broke out in Naples. Here, Frenchmen
1 CONT found in the streets were massacred. In November 1285 Constance's husband died
1 CONT at Villafranca de Penadres where he was buried. His being gracious had made a
1 CONT good impression in Sicily but he had also been too cautious. Pope Honorious IV
1 CONT now decided it was time to restore peace in Italy, but also wanted Sicily
1 CONT returned to the House of Anjou as it had been a previous pope who had made
1 CONT Charles of Anjou its king. The Sicilians, however, were distrustful of the
1 CONT generous promises of the pope and preferred their new king, Constance's son,
1 CONT Jaime, who would become known as "The Just". Jaime was about nineteen years
1 CONT old, whereas the new king of France, Philippe IV "The Fair", was only
1 CONT seventeen. In February 1286 Jaime was crowned at Palermo. Discovering two
1 CONT Dominican friars sent by the pope to start a revolt in Sicily, Jaime
1 CONT courteously sent them back unharmed, as well offering the pope both homage and
1 CONT asking for the confirmation of his title. The pope's response, however, was
1 CONT excommunication for both Constance and Jaime---and, for good measure, all the
1 CONT people of Sicily as well. Constance and Jaime had reached an honourable and
1 CONT just agreement with the imprisoned heir of Charles of Anjou; but the pope,
1 CONT disallowing this, ordered an offensive against Sicily in 1287, a disastrous
1 CONT affair for Honorious IV. When in 1291 her eldest son, Alfonso III "The
1 CONT Liberal", King of Aragon, died childless, it was Jaime, King of Sicily, who
1 CONT became the next King of Aragon. He remained king of both countries until 1296
1 CONT when Fadrique, Constance's third son, became King of Sicily and Jaime remained
1 CONT King of Aragon alone. Constance, having returned to Spain, died in Barcelona
1 CONT in 1301. Source: Leo van de Pas
