1 CONT
1 CONT **Notes**
1 CONT
1 CONT [1] ATL p.44; CAG p.8; GAV p.90
1 CONT
1 CONT [2] Concubines often came from within the circles in which royalty moved, the
1 CONT nobility, and were not only acknowledged as such by the king but also
1 CONT subsequently provided for financially. See Grant of pension approved by the
1 CONT Secrezia on 9.4.1413 (RC 49 p.43v) and 12.1.1417 (RC 52 p.59) to Madonna
1 CONT Tarsia, mistress of Martin the Younger. M. Tarsia was mother of Federico,
1 CONT Martin’s son.
1 CONT
1 CONT [3] The two most important posts granted to prominent Maltese during the
1 CONT Aragonese period was that of Hakem and Castellan. The Castellan controlled the
1 CONT fortress (St Angelo) at the tip of Birgu in the Grand Harbour .The Hakem or
1 CONT Capitano della Verga (Captain of the Rod) had a threefold function. He was
1 CONT Governor of Mdina, then the capital city, he was head of the militia and High
1 CONT Judge with jurisdiction over all courts on the island of Malta apart from
1 CONT Birgu which was the Castellan’s province.
1 CONT
1 CONT [4] RC 1365: Royal grant by Federico III dated 7.4.1365 to Giacomo de
1 CONT Pellegrino in which he is referred to as the husband of Margarita d’Aragona.
1 CONT
1 CONT [5] CAN - Misc. 209. ff 29-38 She made her will on 5.6.1418 which was opened
1 CONT on 14.6.1418 indicating that she died between those two dates.
1 CONT
