0 @N00575@ NOTE geni:about_me \- <https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giacomo_de_Pellegrino> \-
1 CONT Viene da una nobile famiglia di Messina. In data sconosciuta, **sposa
1 CONT Margherita d'Aragona (...-1418)** , - Avevano almeno 3 ragazze:
1 CONT
1 CONT   1. Francia,
1 CONT
1 CONT   2. Cesarea
1 CONT
1 CONT   3. Eleonora.
1 CONT \--------
1 CONT Taken from Maltese Notarial Acts:
1 CONT * Giacomo 'Milite' fils de Giovanni Capitan del Castello nel 1360
1 CONT * Giacomo 'Soldier' son of Giovanni and Capitan of Castello (possibly referring to Mdina) in 1360
1 CONT
1 CONT G.F. Abela also confirms that Giacomo's father was Giovanni Pellegrino from
1 CONT Messina
1 CONT
1 CONT \----
1 CONT "Giacomo de Pellegrino, a Messinese who had settled in Malta, and who from
1 CONT 1356 to 1372 holding various titles and administrative positions along with a
1 CONT lucrative cotton cloth warehouse along with a privateering business took over
1 CONT the politics of the fiefdom. He was finally removed from power after an
1 CONT invasion of Malta from an allied force of Genoese and Sicilian navies and a
1 CONT 2-month siege of Mdina by both these forces and Maltese rebels from both
1 CONT peasants and other noblemen. his power in local politics and administration
1 CONT made him many enemies on the islands and with the Sicilian claimants to the
1 CONT county, while his privateering business made him enemies in both Sicily and
1 CONT Genoa"
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT [milite, Hakem De Malte 1365]
