1 CONT KING OF THE MAGYARS 1270-1272
1 CONT King Stephen V of Hungary #1233
1 CONT [http://trees.ancestry.com/rd?f=document&guid=60eaf22f-66ee-4d6c-9ffd-c66a17ae3deb&tid=10145763&pid=-325889676](http://trees.ancestry.com/rd?f=document&guid=60eaf22f-66ee-4d6c-9ffd-c66a17ae3deb&tid=10145763&pid=-325889676)
1 CONT As crown prince, Stephen assisted his father in bringing the war against
1 CONT the Mongol invaders to a victorious conclusion. In 1260 he was hurt in a
1 CONT battle against Ottokar II, king of Bohemia (1230-78), in which the
1 CONT Hungarians were defeated and forced to surrender Styria (now part of
1 CONT Austria), a region that had been partly under his rule. Stephen thereafter
1 CONT compelled his father to cede a large part of Hungary to him for his sole
1 CONT rule. Stephen invaded Bulgaria in 1268 and assumed the title of king of
1 CONT Bulgaria. On the death of Béla in 1270, he succeeded to the Hungarian
1 CONT throne. In the following year he repulsed an invasion by Ottokar.
1 CONT He ruled from 1270 to 1272. He resisted the invasion of teh Bohemian,
1 CONT Premislaus. He was murdered upon setting out to find his kidnapped son,
1 CONT Ladislas IV.
