1 CONT   * <http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/NEAPOLITAN%20NOBILITY.htm#GodefroiRagusaB>
1 CONT
1 CONT 2\. **SILVESTRE** (-after 1166). "Geoffroi de Raguse, fils du comte Roger" is
1 CONT named with his three sons in a charter dated 1120[38]. Chalandon says that
1 CONT Silvestre de Marsico was the son of "Geoffroi de Raguse, fils du comte Roger
1 CONT I"[39]. The primary source which confirms his parentage has not yet been
1 CONT identified. He was invested as Conte di Marsico in [1150] by Roger I King of
1 CONT Sicily. Hugo Falcandus names "Count Silvester" describing him as "the most
1 CONT timid of men" and one of the nobles in Sicily whose survival was attributable
1 CONT to their unwillingness to move against chancellor Maio[40]. The "Catalogus
1 CONT Baronum", dated to [1168], records "Guillelmus filius Henrici de Sancto
1 CONT Severino" holding "demanium eius de Sancto Severino…de Principatu", with
1 CONT "milites XIII et augmentum eius milites XIV…una…inter feudum et augmentum
1 CONT milites XXVIII", adding in a later passage that "comes Silvester tenet eium in
1 CONT servitio"[41]. The same source records "comes Silvester de Marsico" holding
1 CONT fees "in demanio Marsicum…Roccettam…et Dianum…et Salam…" in "de Marsico", with
1 CONT "militum XXXVI et augmentum eius milites LXXII"[42].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** \---. The name of Silvestre's wife is not known. Silvestre & his wife
1 CONT had four children:
1 CONT
