1 CONT expeditions into Languedoc to support Simon de Montfort in 1215, and Amaury de
1 CONT Montfort in 1219, and again in 1222 he sent Amaury de Montfort two hundred
1 CONT knights and ten thousand foot soldiers under the Archbishop of Bourges and the
1 CONT Count of La Marche. He foresaw that the French monarchy would profit by the
1 CONT defeat of the Albigenses.
