1 CONT OR "AUGUSTUS"; KING OF FRANCE 1180-1223 (BECAME KING 9/18/1180); DIED OF
1 CONT MALARIA
1 CONT Philip II (1165-1223), better known as Philip Augustus, king of France, came
1 CONT to the throne in 1180. He steadily pursued a policy of consolidation, checking
1 CONT the great nobles, and adding fresh territory to his kingdom. Taking advantage
1 CONT of John�s weakness and unpopularity, he conquered Normandy in 1204, and Anjou,
1 CONT Touraine, and Poitou shortly afterward. The victory of Simon de Montfort over
1 CONT the Albigensians and their allies at Muret in 1213 ensured the final victory
1 CONT of the French monarchy in Languedoc. Philip strengthened and thoroughly
1 CONT reorganized the central and local administrative arrangements, and established
1 CONT a council of able officials to aid him in the government. His support and
1 CONT improvement of the towns was a marked feature of his reign. Paris made immense
1 CONT progress, and many charters were granted to other cities. On his death France
1 CONT was one of the great states of Europe, and the royal power was firmly
1 CONT established. [The Home University Encyclopedia, 1946]
