1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla also went by the name
1 CONT of Alfonso VIII "the Noble". He was born on 11 November 1155 at Soria, Castile
1 CONT - León, Spain.4,5 He was the son of Sancho III Alfonsez "el Deseado", rey de
1 CONT Castilla and Princess Blanche Garcés de Navarre.3 King of Castile at Spain
1 CONT between 1158 and 1214.6,7 Styled Rex Toleti et Castelle.8 A contract for the
1 CONT marriage of Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla and reina
1 CONT de Castilla Eleanor d' Anjou was signed in 1169 at Burgos, Castile - León,
1 CONT Spain. Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla married reina
1 CONT de Castilla Eleanor d' Anjou, daughter of Henri II "Courtmanteau", roi d'
1 CONT Angleterre and Aliénor d' Aquitaine, reine d' Angleterre, on 22 September 1177
1 CONT at Burgos, Spain.4,9,3 Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla
1 CONT and Alfonso II "el Casto" , rey de Aragón y Cataluña were made a pact in 1179.
1 CONT This pact of Cazorla fixed the future zones of reconquest for the two
1 CONT countries. Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla and reina
1 CONT de Castilla Eleanor d' Anjou were founded the Monasterio de las Huelgas, a
1 CONT Cistercian monastery, in 1187 at Burgos, Castile - León, Spain. Alfonso VIII
1 CONT Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla abandoned at the last minute by the
1 CONT fellow Christian Kingdoms of Navarre and Leon (ruled by a cousin) which led to
1 CONT a great Muslim victory in 1195 at the Battle of Alarcos.10 He was defeated by
1 CONT Abû Yûsuf Ya'qûb of the Almohads, a new Berber dynasty which invaded the
1 CONT muslim power vacuum in al-Andalus, in Alarcos, on the Córdoba-Toledo road in
1 CONT July 1195 at the Battle of Alarcos.11 Alfonso VIII of Castile, with the
1 CONT assistance of Sancho VII of Navarre, and Pedro II of Aragon, joined by troops
1 CONT from Portugal and Leon (but not the King, Alfonso the Barbarian, who again
1 CONT betrayed Castile), led a victory against the Moors which was the culmination
1 CONT of the Reconquest of Spain by the Christians. On 16 July 1212 at the Battle of
1 CONT Las Navas de Tolosa. He was a witness where Alfonso IX "el Barboro", rey de
1 CONT León repeated his betrayal against his cousin's kingdom of Castile, but this
1 CONT time Castile was saved by others, on 16 July 1212 at the Battle of Las Navas
1 CONT de Tolosa.10 Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla was able,
1 CONT with the assistance of fellow Christian Kingdoms, to finally defeat the
1 CONT Almohads decisively at the Battle of Las Navas de Tolosa, near Bailén in
1 CONT northern Andalusia, the same spot where Scipio had defeated the Carthaginians
1 CONT more than a millennium before, on 16 July 1212.11 He died on 6 October 1214 at
1 CONT Gutierra Munoz, Avila, Castile, Spain, at age 58 years, 10 months and 25
1 CONT days.4,3,5 He was the predecessor of rey de Castilla Henrique I Alfonsez; King
1 CONT of Castile.6,7 Alfonso VIII Sánchez "el de Las Navas", rey de Castilla was
1 CONT buried in the Monasterio de las Huelgas, Burgos, Castile - León, Spain.
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT
1 CONT Nació el 11-XI-1155, en Soria. Fue rey de Castilla de 1158 a 1214. Casó, el
1 CONT 22-IX-1177, en Burgos, Castilla, con Leonor de Plantagenet (1162-1214),
1 CONT princesa de Inglaterra (ver Casa de Anjou-Plantagenet y Reyes de Inglaterra de
1 CONT la Casa de Wessex). Tuvieron diez hijos: Sancho, Fernando, Enrique I —rey de
1 CONT Castilla de 1214 a 1217—, Berenguela (que sigue), Sancha, Urraca (casada con
1 CONT Alfonso II de Portugal), Blanca (casada con Luis VIII de Francia), Mafalda,
1 CONT Leonor (casada con Jaime I de Aragón) y Constanza (abadesa de las Huelgas).
1 CONT Alfonso VIII murió en Gutierre de Muñóz, Ávila, Castilla, el 6-X-1214. Está
1 CONT enterrado, con su esposa (que murió el 25-X-1214), en el Monasterio de las
1 CONT Huelgas, Burgos.
1 CONT
