1 CONT Alfonso VIII (1155-1214), king of Castile (1158-1214); he succeeded to the
1 CONT throne on the death of his father, Sancho III (circa 1134-58). Troubled by
1 CONT interference from Navarre in his youth, he later allied Castile with
1 CONT Aragón, forming a connection that was eventually to become the basis for
1 CONT the unification of Spain. He also established Castilian dominance over
1 CONT León. In 1170 he married Eleanor (died 1214), daughter of King Henry II of
1 CONT England. From the 1170s, he resisted encroachments by the Almohads, Muslim
1 CONT invaders from northern Africa. Defeated by the Muslim caliph Yakub
1 CONT al-Mansur (circa 1160-99) at Alarcos in 1195, Alfonso and his allies won a
1 CONT major victory over the Muslim commander al-Nasir (1158-1225) at Navas de
1 CONT Tolosa in 1212.
1 CONT Afonso VIII de Castela, o Nobre, ou o das Navas (Sória, 11 de Novembro de 1155
1 CONT - Gutierre-Muñoz, 5 de Outubro de 1214), foi rei de Castela e de Toledo desde
1 CONT 1158 até à sua morte.
1 CONT É lembrado principalmente pelo seu papel na Reconquista, levando à queda do
1 CONT califado almóada. Depois de uma pesada derrota em Alarcos, liderou uma
1 CONT coligação de forças cristãs na Batalha de Navas de Tolosa, evento que marcou o
1 CONT início da supremacia cristã na Península Ibérica.
1 CONT O seu reinado também foi marcado pelo domínio de Castela sobre Leão e pela
1 CONT aliança com Aragão, tornando o seu reino o mais poderoso da região.
1 CONT Caused the downfall of Almohad Caliphate. He led a Coalition of christian
1 CONT princes and foreign crusaders who broke the power of the Almohads in 1212. It
1 CONT was the beginning of the end for the Mohammedans in Spain.
1 CONT An interesting story arises within Alfonso's life. It concerns his paramour,
1 CONT Rahel la Fermosa. It is said that she was Jewish. Her name Rahel la Fermosa is
1 CONT Ladino for Rachel the Beautiful.
1 CONT Historical accounts say that she was slaughtered right before the king's eyes
1 CONT at court by nobels.
1 CONT One wonders if this Sephardim woman had any children with Alfonso. If they
1 CONT survived or met the same fate as their mother did.
1 CONT Source: "Fermosa" Jewish encyclopedia, Funk and Wagnalls 1901-1906.
1 CONT King of Castile de Leon. Called, El Baboso because he would froth at the mouth
1 CONT when angered
