1 CONT Alfonso IX, (b. 1171, Zamora, Leon--d. Sept. 24, 1230, Villanueva deSarria,
1 CONT Galicia), king of Leon from 1188 to 1230, son of Ferdinand II ofLeon and first
1 CONT cousin of Alphonso VIII de Castile, and numbered next tohim as being a junior
1 CONT member of the family, is said by Ibn Khaldun tohave been called the "Baboso"
1 CONT or Slobberer, because he was subject tofits of rage, during which he foamed at
1 CONT the mouth. Though he took a partin the work of the reconquest, this king is
1 CONT chiefly remembered by thedifficulties into which his successive marriages led
1 CONT him with the pope.He was first married to his cousin, Teresa of Portugal, who
1 CONT bore him twodaughters and a son who died young. The marriage was declared null
1 CONT by thepope, to whom Alphonso paid no attention till he was presumably tired
1 CONT ofhis wife. It cannot have been his conscience which constrained him toleave
1 CONT Teresa, for his next step was to marry Berengaria de Castile, whowas his
1 CONT second cousin. For this act of contumacy the king and kingdomwere placed under
1 CONT interdict. The pope was, however, compelled to modifyhis measures by the
1 CONT threat that if the people could not obtain theservices of religion they would
1 CONT not support the clergy, and that heresywould spread. The king was left under
1 CONT interdict personally, but to thathe showed himself indifferent, and he had the
1 CONT support of his clergy.Berengaria left him after the birth of five children,
1 CONT and the king thenreturned to Teresa, to whose daughters he left his kingdom by
1 CONT will.[Encyclopaedia Britannica, 1961 ed., Vol. 1, p. 688, ALPHONSO IX of Leon]
