1 CONT Alfonso IX (1166?-1230), king of Leon (1188-1230). In 1197 he married
1 CONT Berengaria (1171-1246), daughter of his first cousin King Alfonso VIII of
1 CONT Castile and granddaughter of King Henry II of England. Pope Innocent III
1 CONT annulled the marriage in 1214 because of the family relationship of
1 CONT Alfonso and Berengaria. Alfonso founded the University of Salamanca and
1 CONT captured Caceres, Badajoz, and Merida from the Muslim Almohads.
1 CONT Alfonso IX, 1171-1230, Spanish king of Leon (1188-1230), son and successor of
1 CONT Ferdinand II. He conquerored from the Moors several cities in Estremadura and
1 CONT was frequently at war with Alfonso VIII of Castile. His marriages with Teresa
1 CONT of Portugal and Berenguela of Castile were both annulled by the pope. He
1 CONT defeated (1230) the Moors at Mérida. His son by Berenguela, Ferdinand III,
1 CONT reunited (1230) Leon and Castile. [The Illustrated Columbia Encyclopedia, 3rd
1 CONT ed., 1969]
1 CONT KING OF LEON; HAD 2 DAUGHTERS AND A SON WHO DIED AT AN EARLY AGE; 1198
