1 CONT Primo y yerno del Rey Alfonso VIII "El de las Navas", hijo del Rey Fernando II
1 CONT de León y padre del Rey Fernando III, unificador de Castilla y León. Subió
1 CONT al trono en 1188. Conquistó Mérida a los musulmanes.-
1 CONT Founded the university of Palencia in 1209-the first of the Spanish
1 CONT universities.
1 CONT He endowed the royal abbey of Las Huelgas, near Burgos, in 1187, at his wife's
1 CONT request; the abbey was also to be their royal mausoleum. In 1195 Alfonso was
1 CONT defeated by the Moors at Alarcos, and Castile was invaded by the armies of
1 CONT neighboring Leon and Navarre, but he fought back and forced their leaders to
1 CONT terms. In 1212 he led Leon and Navarre to a great victory over the Moors at
1 CONT Las Navas de Tolosa. [Cope.FTW]
