1 CONT 1214, Burgos, Castile byname El De Las Navas (Spanish: He of Las Navas) king
1 CONT of Castile from 1158, son of Sancho III, whom he succeeded when three years
1 CONT old. Before Alfonso came of age his reign was troubled by internal strife and
1 CONT the intervention of the kingdom of Navarre in Castilian affairs. Throughout
1 CONT his reign he maintained a close alliance with the kingdom of Aragon, and in
1 CONT 1179 he concluded the Pact of Cazorla, which settled the future line of
1 CONT demarcation between Castile and Aragon when the reconquest of Moorish Spain
1 CONT was completed. From 1172 to 1212 he was engaged in resistance to the Moorish
1 CONT Almohad invaders, who defeated him in 1195. In the same year the kings of Leon
1 CONT and Navarre invaded Castile, but Alfonso defeated them with the aid of King
1 CONT Peter II of Aragon. In 1212 Alfonso secured a great victory at Las Navas de
1 CONT Tolosa over the Almohad sultan and thereby broke Almohad power in Spain.
1 CONT =========================================================== Alfonso VIII, King
1 CONT of Castile 1158-1214 (1155-1214) Born 11 November 1155 Died 6 October 1214
1 CONT Burgos Married September 1177 Burgos Eleanor of England Born 13 October 1162
1 CONT Domfront, Normandy Died 31 October 1214 Burgos As a three-year-old he became
1 CONT king and, after a chaotic period, assumed control of his kingdom in 1166. In
1 CONT Burgos, in September 1177, he married the fifteen-year-old Eleanor, daughter
1 CONT of Henry II of England. Gascony was to be her dowry; but when he claimed this
1 CONT territory in 1204, he lost it to his brother-in-law, John, King of England.
1 CONT The Moors defeated him at Alarcos in 1195 but, after their ininitial incursion
1 CONT into Leon and Navarre, he forced them back and made peace. However, with the
1 CONT kings of Leon and Navarre, he soundly defeated the Moors in 1212 at Las Navas
1 CONT de Tolosa. He died in Burgos on 6 October 1214, followed by his Queen on the
1 CONT 24th, and together they found their last resting place in the Abbey of Las
1 CONT Huelgas which, in 1187, on his wife's request, he had enriched. Source: Leo
1 CONT van de Pas
