1 CONT Alfonso VIII of Castile
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso VIII (11 November 1155 – 5 October 1214), called the Noble or Él de
1 CONT las Navas, was the King of Castile from 1158 to his death. He is most
1 CONT remembered for his part in the Reconquista and the downfall of the Almohad
1 CONT Caliphate. After having suffered a great defeat with his own army at Alarcos
1 CONT against the Almohads, he led the coalition of Christian princes and foreign
1 CONT crusaders who broke the power of the Almohads in the Battle of the Navas de
1 CONT Tolosa in 1212, an event which marked the arrival of an irreversible tide of
1 CONT Christian supremacy on the Iberian peninsula.
1 CONT
1 CONT His reign saw the domination of Castile over León and, by his alliance with
1 CONT Aragon, he drew those two spheres of Christian Iberia into close connection.
