1 CONT GIVN Alfonso VIII of
1 CONT SURN Castile
1 CONT Alfonso VIII (Alfonso the Noble), 1155-1214, Spanish king
1 CONT ofCastile(1158-1214), son and successor of Sancho III. Chaos
1 CONT prevailedduringhis minority, but he quickly restored order after assuming
1 CONT thegovernment. He married Eleanor, daughter of Henry II of England,andtheir
1 CONT daughter, Blanche of Castile, married Louis VIII ofFrance.Alfonso took Cuenca
1 CONT (1177) and incorporated the provinces of
1 CONT ãa„“lava andGuipzèi¸Øcoa into Castile (1200). Attacked simultaneously by
1 CONT acoalitionof Navarre, Aragon, and Leon and by the Moors, he was
1 CONT defeated(1195)by the Moors. He later made peace with his former
1 CONT Christian enemiesand led them to the great victory over the Almohades atNavas
1 CONT deTolosa (1212). At Palencia he founded the first university inSpain(1212 or
1 CONT 1214). He was succeeded by his son, Henry
1 CONT I (1214-17), whowas succeeded by Ferdinand III. [The
1 CONT IllustratedColumbiaEncyclopedia, 1969]
