1 CONT !PROGENY: Sancho of CASTILLE; Berengaria, Queen of Castille; Uracca
1 CONT ofCASTILLE; Constancia of CASTILLE; Matilda of CASTILLE; Sancha ofCASTILLE;
1 CONT Enrique of CASTILLE; and Blanche of CASTILLE.
1 CONT He succeeded to the
1 CONT throne at the age of 3. His minority was troubled by internal strife,
1 CONT however his reign was characterised by a close alliance with Aragon & in
1 CONT 1179 he concluded the pact of Cazorla which settled the future line of
1 CONT demarcation between Castile & Aragon when the conquest of Moorish Spainwas
1 CONT completed. The main task of Alfonso's reign was resistance to the Almohad
1 CONT invaders who by 1172 had secured control over most of the Moorish states.
1 CONT In 1195 they inflicted a great defeat on him at Alarcos, while incollusion
1 CONT with them the Kings of Leon & Navarre invaded Castile. However he dealt
1 CONT with Leon & Navarre, forcing the king of Leon to marry his daughter. In
1 CONT 1212 he finally secured a great victory over the Almohad sultan whichbroke
1 CONT Almohad power in Spain. M 1176 Eleanor (1161-1214), d. of Henry II,King
1 CONT of England (See ENGLAND). Died 6 Oct. 1214. He had issue: Weis, pp102 &
1 CONT 104 Stuart, p 44 EB, I, p 593 Leese, p 47
