1 CONT
1 CONT 1156
1 CONT
1 CONT 1155-1214. Son of Sancho III of Castile; king of Castile(1166-1214).After a
1 CONT chaotic minority, Alfonso assumed controlof his kingdom in 1166and married
1 CONT Eleanor, daughter of Henry IIof England, in 1169. Hereceived the reversion of
1 CONT Gascony andas her dowry, but in 1204 on thedeath of Eleanor of Aquitainehad to
1 CONT claim it by force, later losing it toKing John ofEngland. He endowed the royal
1 CONT abbey of Las Huelgas,nearBurgos, in 1187, at his wife's request; the abbey was
1 CONT also to betheirroyal mausoleum. In 1195 Alfonso was defeated by theMoors at
1 CONT Alarcos,and Castile was invaded by the armies ofneighbouring Leon and
1 CONT Navarre,but he fought back and forcedtheir leaders to terms. In 1212 he led
1 CONT Leonand Navarre to agreat victory over the Moors at Las Navas de Tolosa.
1 CONT As a three-year-old he became king and, after a chaotic period, assume d
1 CONT control of his kingdom in 1166. In Burgos, in September 1177, he mar ried the
1 CONT fifteen-year-old Eleanor, daughter of Henry II of England. Ga scony was to be
1 CONT her dowry; but when he claimed this territory in 1204 , he lost it to his
1 CONT brother-in-law, John, King of England.
1 CONT
1 CONT The Moors defeated him at Alarcos in 1195 but, after their ininitial i
1 CONT ncursion into Leon and Navarre, he forced them back and made peace. Ho wever,
1 CONT with the kings of Leon and Navarre, he soundly defeated the Moo rs in 1212 at
1 CONT Las Navas de Tolosa.
1 CONT
1 CONT He died in Burgos on 6 October 1214, followed by his Queen on the 24th , and
1 CONT together they found their last resting place in the Abbey of La s Huelgas
1 CONT which, in 1187, on his wife's request, he had enriched.
1 CONT NOTE
1 CONT GEDCOM created by TMG...
1 CONT September 1177:
1 CONT At age 22 married Eleanor Plantagenet, age 15
1 CONT The son of Ferdinand II of Leon, he allied with Almohads to regain lands lost
1 CONT by his cousin Alfonso VIII of Castile; as a result ordered by papal interdict
1 CONT to marry (1197) Beregaria of Castile.
1 CONT King of Wessex ( 957 - 959)
1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso IX (1171-1230), king of Leon from 1188-1230, granted rights to
1 CONT assembly of nobles certain rights, including the rights to life,
1 CONT honor, home, and property along with the right to a fair trial.
