1 CONT Alfonso II (Aragon) or Alfons I (Provence and Barcelona) (Huesca, 1157 –
1 CONT Perpignan, 25 April 1196), called the Chaste or the Troubadour, was the King
1 CONT of Aragon and Count of Barcelona from 1162 until his death. He was the son of
1 CONT Ramon Berenguer IV of Barcelona and Petronilla of Aragon and the first King of
1 CONT Aragon who was also Count of Barcelona.
1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso II, Prince of Aragon, b. ca. 1176 in Zaragoza, Spain, d. February 1209
1 CONT in Palermo, Sicily, Italy
1 CONT
1 CONT Father: Alfonso II "the Chaste", King of Aragon, b. 1152 in Huesca, Spain, d.
1 CONT 25 April 1196 in Perpignan, Pyrenees-Orientales, France
1 CONT
1 CONT Mother: Sancha of Castile, b. 21 September 1154 in Toledo, Castile, Spain, d.
1 CONT 9 November 1208 in Jaen, Spain
1 CONT
1 CONT Spouse: Gersinde de Sabran
1 CONT
1 CONT Married July 1193.
1 CONT
1 CONT Children:
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Ramon V, Count of Provence, b. ca. 1194 in Provence, France, m. Beatrice of Savoy, 1219/20 in Chambery, Savoy, france, d. 19 August 1245 in France
