1 CONT Alfonso II ( 1174-1 Dec 1269) was the second son of Alfonso II of Aragon and
1 CONT Sancha of Castile. His father transferred the County of Provence from his
1 CONT uncle Sancho to him in 1185. Alfonso II was born in Barcelona, Barcelona,
1 CONT Catalonia, Spain
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1193, Alfonso married Gersenda II of Sabran, daughter of Rainou, Count of
1 CONT Forcalquier and Gersend of Forcalquier. They had a child who became Ramon
1 CONT Berenguer IV as count of Provence.
1 CONT
1 CONT According to explanations in the manuscripts of Gaucelm Faidit's poems,
1 CONT Alfonso was a rival of the troubadour's for the love of Jourdaine d'Embrun.
1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso II died in Palermo, Sicily, Italy.
