1 CONT Alfonso II, Count of Provence
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso II (died 1209) was the second son of Alfonso II of Aragon and Sancha
1 CONT of Castile. His father transferred the County of Provence from his uncle
1 CONT Sancho to him in 1185.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1193, Alfonso married Gersenda II of Sabran, daughter of Rainou, Count of
1 CONT Forcalquier and Gersend of Forcalquier. They had a child who became Ramon
1 CONT Berenguer IV as count of Provence.
1 CONT
1 CONT According to explanations in the manuscripts of Gaucelm Faidit's poems,
1 CONT Alfonso was a rival of the troubadour's for the love of Jourdaine d'Embrun.[1]
1 CONT
1 CONT Alfonso II died in Palermo, Sicily, Italy.
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit] Notes
1 CONT ^ Biographies des troubadours ed. J. Boutière, A.-H. Schutz (Paris: Nizet,
1 CONT 1964) pp. 187-191.
