1 CONT
1 CONT Also called Elizabeth of Bosnia. Erzsebet of the Kumans was born in 1240. She
1 CONT was the daughter of Kuthen, Kahn of the Polowets and N. N. of Galicia.1,2,3
1 CONT Erzsebet of the Kumans married István V, Király Magyarország, son of Béla IV,
1 CONT Király Magyarország and Maria Laskarina, in 1255; His father had him married
1 CONT for political reasons. "In the interests of protecting Christianity," Bela
1 CONT advised the Pope, "we married our first born son to a Cuman girl... to secure
1 CONT the possibility of converting these people to Christianity."4,1 Erzsebet of
1 CONT the Kumans died after 1290.
1 CONT
