1 CONT <http://www.infoplease.com/ce6/society/A0814241.html>
1 CONT
1 CONT Cumans or Kumans (both: kOO'mänz) [key], nomadic East Turkic people,
1 CONT identified with the Kipchaks (or the western branch of the Kipchaks) and known
1 CONT in Russian as Polovtsi. Coming from NW Asian Russia, they conquered S Russia
1 CONT and Walachia in the 11th cent., and for almost two centuries warred
1 CONT intermittently with the Byzantine Empire, Hungary, and Kiev. They founded a
1 CONT nomadic state in the steppes along the Black Sea, and were active in commerce
1 CONT with Central Asia and Venice. In the early 12th cent. the main Cuman forces
1 CONT were defeated by the Eastern Slavs. The Mongols decisively defeated the Cumans
1 CONT c.1245. Some were sold as slaves, and many took refuge in Bulgaria and also in
1 CONT Hungary, where they were gradually assimilated into the Hungarian culture.
1 CONT Others joined the khanate of the Golden Horde (also called the Western
1 CONT Kipchaks), which was organized on the former Cuman territory in Russia.
1 CONT
