1 CONT
1 CONT Isabelle of Hainaut was queen consort of France. For her wedding with Philip
1 CONT Augustus, she brought as her dowry the county of Artois. She was crowned
1 CONT consort of France at Saint Denis on 28 May 1180.
1 CONT
1 CONT Since she was a descendant of Charlemagne, the chroniclers of the time saw in
1 CONT this marriage a union of the Carolingian and Capetian dynasties. Though she
1 CONT received extravagant praise from certain annalists, she failed to win the
1 CONT affections of Philip due to her inability to provide him with an heir.
1 CONT
1 CONT See <http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isabelle_of_Hainaut> for considerably more
1 CONT information, as well as another, certainly prettier (although not necessarily
1 CONT accurate) picture of Isabella.
