0 @N00656@ NOTE geni:about_me <http://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Otto_III._%28K%C3%A4rnten%29>
1 CONT
1 CONT Otto III (c. 1265 † 25 May 1310) was Count of Gorizia and Tyrol and As Otto
1 CONT III Duke of Carinthia and Carniever (1295–1310).
1 CONT
1 CONT Origin- Otto was the son of Duke Meinhard II and Elisabeth of Bavaria. He
1 CONT succeeded his father in his offices after his death in 1295, together with his
1 CONT brothers Albert, Ludwig and Heinrich.
1 CONT
1 CONT Rule-Otto took over a well-organized sovereignty; his father had laid the
1 CONT foundation for an efficient administration with the promotion of the
1 CONT ministerials and the creation of the Tyrolean Raitbücher. Otto first agreed
1 CONT with the Bishop of Brixen on the border of the territories of Tyrol and the
1 CONT diocese, which was henceforth established at the mouth of the Avisio into the
1 CONT Adige, north of Trento. Otto's brothers became bailiffs of the bishops of
1 CONT Trent. Although Otto obtained some Tyrolean customs rights through King
1 CONT Albrecht I, Otto's lavish court put a heavy strain on the budget. Under Otto's
1 CONT measures of domination, the expansion and fortification of the gries market
1 CONT (1305) against the still episcopalally dominated central town of Bolzano stand
1 CONT out.
1 CONT
1 CONT Seal Duke Otto's seal shows a rider blowing to the right with an inlaid lance
1 CONT (with the right-looking Tyrolean eagle on a racing flag) and the shield
1 CONT (divided, Carinthian coat of arms, three armed lions on top of each other on
1 CONT the right, a bar on the left); the two-line transcription between stableists
1 CONT reads: OTTO DEI GRACIA DUX KARINTHIE TIROLIS ET GORICIE COMES AQUILEGENSIS /
1 CONT TRIDENTINE BRISINENSIS ECLESIARU(m) ADUOCATUS; the letters have uncial shapes.
1 CONT
1 CONT Family In 1297 Otto married Duchess Euphemia (1281–1347), daughter of Duke
1 CONT Henry V of Silesia. With her he had four daughters: Anna, * 1300, who married
1 CONT Count Palatine Rudolf II; Elizabeth, later wife of King Peter II of Sicily;
1 CONT Ursula and Euphemia. Since Otto died without sons, his younger brother Henry
1 CONT of Carinthia succeeded him in 1310; the brothers Albert and Louis had already
1 CONT died in 1292 and 1305 respectively.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT Otto III. (* um 1265; † 25. Mai 1310) aus dem Geschlecht der Meinhardiner war
1 CONT Graf von Görz und Tirol und als Otto III. Herzog von Kärnten (1295-1310).
1 CONT
