1 CONT
1 CONT OTTO von Görz (-28 May 1310). He succeeded his father in 1295 as OTTO Duke of
1 CONT Carinthia. "Otto, Ludovicus et Heinricus…duces Karinthie, comites Goricie et
1 CONT Tyrolis" confirmed protection over Tirol Neustift by charter dated 1297[812].
1 CONT His parentage is confirmed by the charter dated 1298 under which "Otto…Dux
1 CONT Karinthie, Comes Tyrolis et Goricie" confirmed a donation to Benedictbeuern by
1 CONT "bone memorie Dominus Meinhardus Dux Karinthie genitor noster"[813]. "Otto,
1 CONT Ludovicus et Heinricus…duces Karinthie, comites Goricie et Tyrolis,
1 CONT Aquilegiensis, Tridentine et Brixinensis ecclesiarum advocati" confirmed
1 CONT protection over Tirol Neustift, in memory of "comite Alberto proavo nostro nec
1 CONT non duce Meinhardo genitore nostro", by charter dated 1302[814]. The necrology
1 CONT of Stams records the death "VI Kal Jun" of "dominus Otto illustris dux
1 CONT Carinthie primogenitus fundatoris nostri"[815]. m ([1300]) EUPHEMIA von
1 CONT Liegnitz, daughter of HEINRICH V "the Fat" Duke of Liegnitz [Piast] & his wife
1 CONT Elźbieta of Poland [Piast] ([1278/83]-Jun 1347). As a widow, she was lady of
1 CONT Wangen, Sansheim and Castelruth[816]. Duke Otto & his wife had four children:
1 CONT
1 CONT a) ELISABETH (-1352 or after). Regent of Sicily 1348-1352 for her minor son. m
1 CONT (23 Apr 1322) PIETRO of Sicily, son of FEDERIGO I King of Sicily [Aragon] &
1 CONT his wife Eléonore of Sicily [Anjou-Capet] (1304-Calataxibeta 15 Aug 1342). He
1 CONT succeeded his father in 1338 as PIETRO II King of Sicily.
1 CONT
1 CONT b) ANNA ([1300]-[16 May 1331/4 Jul 1335], [26 Jun \----], bur Schönau). The
1 CONT Notæ Fuerstenfeldenses record the marriage of "filiam ducis Karinthie dictam
1 CONT de Sarentein" and Duke Rudolf[817]. The necrology of Seligenthal records the
1 CONT death "VI Kal Jun" of "Anna coma Reni ducissa Bavarie"[818]. m (1328) as his
1 CONT first wife, RUDOLF Pfalzgraf, son of RUDOLF I joint Duke of Upper Bavaria and
1 CONT joint Pfalzgraf bei Rhein & his wife Mechtild von Nassau (Wolfratshausen 8 Aug
1 CONT 1306-Neustadt 4 Oct 1353, bur Neustadt St Aegidius). He succeeded in 1329 as
1 CONT RUDOLF II "der Blinde" Pfalzgraf bei Rhein und in der Oberpfalz.
1 CONT
1 CONT c) URSULA (-1327).
1 CONT
1 CONT d) EUPHEMIA (-[28 Apr 1329/1330]).
