1 CONT
1 CONT 4\. GUGLIELMO of Sicily (1312-Valencia 22 Aug 1338, bur Palermo). Principe di
1 CONT Tarento. He succeeded his brother Manfredo in 1317 as Duke of Athens, although
1 CONT he never visited the territory. He added the title Duke of Neopatras in 1319,
1 CONT after his half-brother Alfonso Fadrique captured the town and large parts of
1 CONT Thessaly[328]. A charter dated 5 Apr 1331 records a peace agreement relating
1 CONT to the island of Eubœa and names "domini Guilielmi duchatuum Athenarum et
1 CONT Neupatrie ducis…domini Frederici Sicilie regis…filii" acting with the advice
1 CONT of "Alfonsum Friderici, insularum Melineti et Gaudisii comitem, dicti…regis
1 CONT Friderici filium"[329].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** (1335) as her first husband, MARÍA Álvarez de Ejérica, daughter of JAIME
1 CONT de Aragón Barón de Ejérica & his wife doña Beatriz de Lauria Señora de
1 CONT Cocentaina ([1310]-before 1364). She married secondly (Valencia 1338) as his
1 CONT second wife, Infante don Ramón Berenguer de Aragón Conde de Prades, later
1 CONT Conde de Ampurias.
