1 CONT 1189-1233. He was the son of Humbert III of Savoy and Beatrice of Viennois.
1 CONT His birth was seen as miraculous; his monkish father had despaired of having a
1 CONT male heir after three wives. Count Humbert sought counsel from St. Anthelm,
1 CONT who blessed Humbert three times, and it was seen as a prophecy come true when
1 CONT Thomas was born shortly after Anthelm himself died on June 26, 1178. He was
1 CONT named in honor of St. Thomas Becket.
1 CONT Thomas possessed the martial abilities, energy, and brilliance that his father
1 CONT lacked, and Savoy enjoyed a golden age under his leadership. He had taken over
1 CONT effective rule of Savoy by August 1191, and despite his youth he began the
1 CONT push north-west into new territories. He conquerored Vaud, Bugey, and
1 CONT Carignano. He supported the Hohenstaufens, and was known as "Thomas the
1 CONT Ghibelline" due to his career as Imperial Vicar of Lombardy.
1 CONT In 1195 he ambushed the party of Count William I of Geneva, which was
1 CONT escorting the count's daughter, Marguerite, to France for her intended wedding
1 CONT to King Philip II of France. Thomas carried off Marguerite and married her
1 CONT himself, producing some eight sons and six daughters.
