1 CONT Name Suffix: [QUEEN OF CASTIL
1 CONT Ancestral File Number: 8XJ3-Z8
1 CONT Daughter of Henry II of England and Eleanor of Aquitaine. In 1176 she married
1 CONT Alfonso VIII, king of Castile. He was promised Gascony as her dowry and seized
1 CONT it by force in 1204 after Eleanor of Aquitaine's death. His brother-in-law,
1 CONT King John of England, recaptured it in 1206. The Cistercian royal nunnery of
1 CONT Las Huelgas in Castile was founded in 1187 at Eleanor's request. It is built
1 CONT in a similar style to buildings in Angers, her birthplace, suggesting that
1 CONT Eleanor may have employed an Angevin architect. She and Alfonso were buried
1 CONT there.
1 CONT _P_CCINFO 1-20792
1 CONT _P_CCINFO 1-887
1 CONT Eleanor (Eleanora) Plantaganet de Castile, born in 1162, died in 1214,promised
1 CONT initially by her father to marry French royalty, but eventuallymarried Afonso
1 CONT VIII. de Castile., King de Castile (1158-1214). He was theson of Sancho III.,
1 CONT the Desired, King de Castile (1157-1158). See thislineage in the Kings of
1 CONT Spain Line in Volume I. Eleanor and Afonso VIII.had the following children
1 CONT (Note: Some differences are seen between thislist and the one in the Kings of
1 CONT Spain Line):
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT 1\. Sancho de Castile.
1 CONT
1 CONT 2\. Bergenuela (Berengaria) de Castile, married Afonso IX, King of Leon.They
1 CONT had a son, Ferdinand III, who married Joanna Dammartin. See thecontinuation of
1 CONT this lineage in the Spanish Kings Line of Volume I.
1 CONT
1 CONT 3\. Uracca de Castile, had been promised to Louis VIII., the heir ofFrance,
1 CONT but eventually married Afonso II. the Fat, King of Portugal,1211-1223. She was
1 CONT rejected by the French because of her unusual name.Her younger sister, Blanche
1 CONT was deemed to be more suitable for the Frenchtastes.
1 CONT
1 CONT 4\. Blanche de Castile, born on March 4, 1188, in the palace of Placentia,in
1 CONT Castile, where she spent most of her childhood years, married on May23, 1200,
1 CONT Louis VIII. of France., prince and heir of France andeventually King of
1 CONT France. Blanche received as her dowry, the town ofEvreux with its surrounding
1 CONT land, always a bone of contention betweenFrance and England, but nevertheless
1 CONT given to her by her father-in-law,King Philip. Her uncle, King John of
1 CONT England, gave her the fiefs ofIssoudun and Grapay in Berry. See the
1 CONT continuation of this lineageelsewhere in Volume I. See Pernoud, "Blanche de
1 CONT Castile," for details onher life and times. Their son was King Louis IX of
1 CONT France.
1 CONT
1 CONT 5\. Constancia de Castile
1 CONT
1 CONT 6\. Matilda de Castile
1 CONT
1 CONT 7\. Sancha de Castile
1 CONT
1 CONT 8\. Enrique de Castile
