1 CONT Eleanor Plantagenet was born on 13 October 1162 at Domfront Castle, Domfront,
1 CONT Normandy, France.2 She was the daughter of Henry II 'Curtmantle' d'Anjou, King
1 CONT of England and Eleanor, Duchesse d'Aquitaine. She married Alfonso VIII, Rey de
1 CONT Castilla, son of Sancho III, Rey de Castilla and Blanche de Navarre, in
1 CONT September 1170 at Burgos Cathedral, Burgos, Castile, Spain.2 She was also
1 CONT reported to have been married in 1177. She died on 31 October 1214 at age 52
1 CONT at Burgos, Castile, Spain.3 She was buried at Abbey of Las Huelgas, Burgos,
1 CONT Castile, Spain.3
