1 CONT Marguerite of Geneva (d.1252) was the daughter of William I, Count of Geneva
1 CONT and Beatrice de Faucigny. She was supposed to become the third wife of Philip
1 CONT II of France but was in 1195 while on her way to Paris she was abducted by
1 CONT Thomas I of Savoy. Thomas then married her himself, claiming that Philip II
1 CONT was already married (the French King had married Ingeborg of Denmark in 1193
1 CONT but had repudiated her soon thereafter)
1 CONT
1 CONT The children of Marguerite and Thomas I of Savoy were:
1 CONT
1 CONT Amadeus IV of Savoy (1197 - 1253)
1 CONT Umberto (d.1223)
1 CONT Thomas, Count of Flanders, count in Piedmont
1 CONT Aimone (d.1237), Lord of Chablais
1 CONT William of Savoy, Bishop of Valence and Dean of Vienne
1 CONT Amadeo of Savoy, Bishop of Maurienne
1 CONT Peter II of Savoy, Earl of Richmond and later disputed count of Savoy
1 CONT Philip I of Savoy, archbishop of Lyon, later Count Palatine of Burgundy by
1 CONT marriageand disputed count of Savoy in 1268
1 CONT Boniface of Savoy, Archbishop of Canterbury
1 CONT Beatrice of Savoy (1205- 4 January 1267), wife of Ramon Berenguer IV, Count of
1 CONT Provence. She was married in 1219 and was mother to four queens consort
1 CONT Alasia of Savoy (d.1250), abbess of St Pierre, Lyon
1 CONT Agatha of Savoy (d.1245), abbess of St Pierre, Lyon
1 CONT Margherita of Savoy (d.1273), wife of Hartmann I of Kyburg
1 CONT Avita of Savoy (1215-92), wife of Baldwin de Redvers, 7th Earl of Devon and
1 CONT later of Robert Aguillon (d.1286)
