1 CONT =Béla IV of Hungary=
1 CONT
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT Béla IV (Hungarian: IV. Béla), (29 November 1206 – 3 May 1270), King of
1 CONT Hungary[1] (1235-1270) and of Croatia (as part of the Hungarian Kingdom)
1 CONT (1235-1270), duke of Styria between 1254-1258. One of the most famous kings of
1 CONT Hungary, distinguished himself through his policy of strenghtening of the
1 CONT royal power following the example of his grand father Bela III, and by the
1 CONT rebuilding Hungary after the catastrophy of the Mongolian invasion in 1241.
1 CONT For this reason was called by the Hungarians "the second founder of our
1 CONT country".
1 CONT
