1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT
1 CONT Béla IV (Hungarian: IV. Béla, (1206 – 3 May 1270), King of Hungary and Croatia
1 CONT (1214-1270), Duke of Styria (1254-1258). Béla was present, at the age of
1 CONT seven, when a group of conspirators killed his mother, and he could never
1 CONT forgive his father's generosity towards the conspirators' accomplices. Shortly
1 CONT afterwards, he was crowned junior king (rex iunior) and he governed several
1 CONT provinces of the Kingdom of Hungary during his father's reign. He endeavoured
1 CONT to restore the royal power that had declined since the death of his
1 CONT grandfather, King Béla, which resulted in permanent conflicts between Béla and
1 CONT his father. When he ascended the throne, he determined to revive his
1 CONT grandfather's internal policy which made him unpopular among his barons.
1 CONT However, he soon had to face the threat of the Mongol invasion of Europe;
1 CONT therefore he granted asylum to the Cumans in order to strengthen his military
1 CONT force. After the Tatar invasion he became one of the most famous Hungarian
1 CONT kings. Nevertheless, the Mongol armies defeated his troops in a decisive
1 CONT battle requiring his escape to the farthest fortress of his kingdom while the
1 CONT Mongols were pillaging the country. When the Mongol troops were withdrawn
1 CONT unexpectedly, Béla returned and commenced reconstruction of his devastated
1 CONT kingdom; he patronized towns, constructed new fortresses and encouraged
1 CONT immigration. His success is reflected by his popular epithet, "the Second
1 CONT Founder of our Country", in Hungary. During the second period of his reign, he
1 CONT proceeded to expand his rule over the neighbouring countries. However his last
1 CONT years were characterized by his permanent conflicts with his eldest son,
1 CONT Stephen.
1 CONT
1 CONT Béla was the eldest son of King Andrew II of Hungary and his first wife,
1 CONT Gertrude of Merania. Upon Pope Innocent III's request, the ecclesiastic and
1 CONT temporal dignitaries of the Kingdom of Hungary took an oath before his birth
1 CONT that they would accept him as his father's successor.
1 CONT
