1 CONT roi de Hongrie (1235-1270)
1 CONT ES II:155
1 CONT King of Hungary
1 CONT RBS : King of Hungary between 1235 and 1270. He was a witness where Kuthen,
1 CONT Kahn of the Polowets was given asylum from the marauding Gengis Khan, with his
1 CONT people, the Cumans, by King Bela IV in 1239. Béla IV, Király Magyarország was
1 CONT routed on the banks of the Sajó River by Mongols under Batu Khan in 1241. Béla
1 CONT fled to Dalmatia, and for a year the kingdom of Hungary did not exist. So
1 CONT nearly complete was the country's destruction that Hungarians, when referring
1 CONT to total calamity, use the word tatárjárás, meaning Tatar invasion. When the
1 CONT Mongols withdrew because of dynastic troubles, Béla began to reconstruct his
1 CONT realm, a task that occupied the rest of his reign. He battled Frederick II,
1 CONT Duke of Austria, who died as a result of the battle on 15 June 1246.
