1 CONT Bela IV , 1206-70, king of Hungary (1235-70), son and successor ofAndrew II.
1 CONT He tried to curtail the power of the magnates and set outto recover the
1 CONT crownlands his father had given to supporters.Confronted by the menace of the
1 CONT Mongol invasion, he sent unheededappeals to Pope Gregory IX and Holy Roman
1 CONT Emperor Frederick II, but hewas crushingly defeated at Mohi on the Sajo River
1 CONT in 1241. Returningafter the withdrawal of the invaders, he repopulated the
1 CONT country byinviting foreign colonization. In a battle (1246) with the
1 CONT lastBabenberg duke of Austria, the duke was killed but the Austrians
1 CONT werevictorious. Bela's long struggle with Ottocar II, king of Bohemia,
1 CONT forAustria and Styria ended (1260) in defeat. His last years weredisturbed by
1 CONT the rebellion of his son, later King Stephen V.
