1 CONT Jean I de Brienne, Emperor of Constantinople was born circa 1148.1 He was the
1 CONT son of Erard II, Comte de Brienne and Agnes de Montfaucon.1 He married,
1 CONT firstly, Maria de Montferrat, Queen of Jerusalem, daughter of Conrad, Marquis
1 CONT de Montferrat and Isabella d'Anjou, Queen of Jerusalem, on 15 September 1210.1
1 CONT He married, secondly, Stephania of Armenia, daughter of Leo II, King of
1 CONT Armenia, in 1214.1 He married, thirdly, Berengaria de Castilla, daughter of
1 CONT Alfonso IX, Rey de Castilla y León and Berengaria de Castilla, in 1223.1 He
1 CONT died on 21 March 1237.1
1 CONT Jean I de Brienne, Emperor of Constantinople fought in the Third Crusade.1 He
1 CONT gained the title of King John of Jerusalem.2 Between 1205 and 1221 he was the
1 CONT Regent of the County of Brienne for his nephew.1 He succeeded to the title of
1 CONT King Jean I of Jerusalem in 1210, in right of his wife, although he reigned at
1 CONT Acre as Jerusalem was in Saracen hands.1 He abdicated as King of Jerusalem in
1 CONT 1212.3 He fought in the Fifth Crusade from 1218 to 1219, which he led.1 He was
1 CONT created Emperor Jean I of Constantinople in 1229.1 He was a Franciscan friar.1
1 CONT Child of Jean I de Brienne, Emperor of Constantinople and Maria de Montferrat,
1 CONT Queen of Jerusalem
