1 CONT John, byname JOHN OF BRIENNE, French JEAN DE BRIENNE (b. c. 1148--d. March
1 CONT 1237, Constantinople), count of Brienne who became titular king of Jerusalem
1 CONT (1210-29) and Latin emperor of Constantinople (1231-37).
1 CONT
1 CONT A penniless younger son of the French count Erard II of Brienne and Agnes of
1 CONT Montbéliard, John passed most of his life as a minor noble until befriended by
1 CONT King Philip II Augustus of France, who arranged for him to marry Mary (Marie)
1 CONT of Montferrat, queen of the crusader state of Jerusalem, in 1210. John reached
1 CONT the Palestinian town of Acre on Sept. 13, 1210, married Mary the following
1 CONT day, and was crowned at Tyre on October 3. Mary died in 1212, and John was
1 CONT named regent for their infant daughter, Yolande de Brienne, who inherited the
1 CONT crown as Isabella II. In 1214 John married Princess Stephanie of Armenia,
1 CONT daughter of the Armenian king Leo II, and later had a son by her.
1 CONT
1 CONT As regent, John arranged a five-year truce with al-Malik al-'Adil, sultan of
1 CONT Egypt and Syria, in July 1212, and during the truce he persuaded Pope Innocent
1 CONT III to launch the Fifth Crusade in support of his daughter's kingdom. In 1218
1 CONT he joined the crusading force from the West in an expedition against the
1 CONT Egyptian port of Damietta. After quarrelling with the crusade leader, the
1 CONT cardinal legate Pelagius, John left Egypt in February 1220, returning in July
1 CONT 1221 to witness the humiliating defeat of the crusaders and the abandonment of
1 CONT the siege of Damietta.
1 CONT
1 CONT Stephanie died in 1219; John then married Berengaria, daughter of Ferdinand
1 CONT III of Castile, and in 1225 gave his daughter Isabella in marriage to the Holy
1 CONT Roman emperor Frederick II, trying to retain his rights as regent of the
1 CONT kingdom of Jerusalem. Immediately following the marriage, however, Frederick
1 CONT began to contest these rights.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1228 John was invited to Constantinople to be regent and co-emperor with
1 CONT the young Baldwin II and arranged a match between Baldwin and his four-year-
1 CONT old daughter by Berengaria. Crowned in 1231, John helped fend off attacks by
1 CONT the Bulgarian tsar Ivan Asen II and the Nicaean emperor John III Vatatzes, but
1 CONT shortly before his death he was forced to appeal to the West for help.
