1 CONT King of Jerusalem. Cypriot nobleman, Count of Brienne.
1 CONT Source:
1 CONT WH Turton: Plantagenet Ancestry: Genealogical Publishing Co. 1928.
1 CONT Charles Mosley Edition Burkes Peerage and Baronage 106th Edition, Vol 1 pg
1 CONT 227.
1 CONT Regent of Jerusalem 1212-1225, Emperor of Constantinople 1228 - 1237.
1 CONT He was also Regent of Jerusalem 1212-1225. And Emperor of Constantinople
1 CONT 1228-1237.
1 CONT John, a French nobleman, became king by his marriage to Queen Marie de
1 CONT Montferrat of Jerusalem. When Marie died, their young daughter Yolande
1 CONT succeeded as queen under John's regency. After playing an important part
1 CONT in the Fifth Crusade, John lived and traveled in western Europe, seeking
1 CONT support for another Crusade. In 1222 he betrothed Yolande to the Holy
1 CONT Roman emperor Frederick II. Upon their marriage in 1225, Frederick quickly
1 CONT claimed the crown of Jerusalem. John, also claiming the crown, commanded
1 CONT papal troops in an attack upon Frederick's possessions in Italy. In 1229
1 CONT John became regent and coemperor with Baldwin II, the 12-year-old Latin
1 CONT ruler of Constantinople. In this capacity, he defended the Latin Empire
1 CONT against attacks by the Byzantines and their Bulgarian allies.
1 CONT King of Jerusalem, Jean de Brienne
