0 @N00724@ NOTE geni:about_me
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT ===Wikipedia===
1 CONT
1 CONT   * English [<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maria_Laskarina> **Maria Laskarina** ]
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Magyar / Hungarian [<http://hu.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laszkarisz_M%C3%A1ria_magyar_kir%C3%A1lyn%C3%A9> **Laszkarisz Mária magyar királyné** ]
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT She was a younger sister of Irene Lascarina, first Empress consort of John III
1 CONT Doukas Vatatzes. Theodore married his eldest daughter to his designated heir
1 CONT in 1212. Theodore was widowed in the same year and proceeded to marriages with
1 CONT Philippa of Armenia and Marie de Courtenay. However John was never displaced
1 CONT in succession.
1 CONT
1 CONT As a younger daughter, the marriage of Maria was not intended to add a
1 CONT potential husband in the line of succession to the throne. Instead it secured
1 CONT a marital alliance with the Kingdom of Hungary.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1218, Maria was married to prince Béla of Hungary. Bride and groom were
1 CONT about twelve-years-old. Her husband was the eldest son of Andrew II of Hungary
1 CONT and Gertrude of Merania.
1 CONT
1 CONT Andrew II died on 26 October 1235. The crown prince succeeded him as Béla IV
1 CONT and Maria became his Queen consort. Béla reigned for thirty-five years and
1 CONT died on 3 May 1270. Maria survived him by about two months.
1 CONT
1 CONT Children
1 CONT
1 CONT Maria and Béla IV of Hungary had ten children:
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Margaret of Hungary (c. 1220 - 20 April 1242). Married Guillaume de Saint-Omer. Her husband is often listed in genealogies as "Lord of Thebes". However he might be confused with Bela de Saint-Omer, an older brother who held the title jure uxori
1 CONC s.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Kunegunda of Hungary (5 March 1224 - 24 July 1292), also known as Kinga. She was married to King Boleslaus V of Poland, after his death becoming a nun and abbess; she was canonized by Pope John Paul II in 1999.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Anna of Hungary (c. 1226 - after 1270). Married Rostislav of Slavonia.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Catherine of Hungary. (c. 1229 - 1242). She died while fleeing with her family following the Battle of Mohi.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Elizabeth of Hungary (c. 1236 - 24 October 1271). Married Henry XIII, Duke of Bavaria.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Constance of Hungary (c. 1237 - after 1252). Married Leo I of Halych.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Yolanda of Hungary (c. 1238 - 1298). Married Boleslaus of Greater Poland. Later became a nun and abbess, who has been declared as a candidate for sainthoood.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Stephen V of Hungary (December, 1239 - 6 August 1272).
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Saint Margaret of Hungary (27 January 1242 - 18 January 1271). Named after an older sister. Canonized by the Roman Catholic Church in 1943, for whom Margaret Island in Budapest is named, having been the place where a royal monastery was establi
1 CONC shed by her parents for her.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Béla, Duke of Slavonia, Croatia and Dalmatia (c. 1243 - 1269). Married Kunigunde of Brandenburg, a daughter of Otto III, Margrave of Brandenburg. His widow married Waleran IV of Limburg.
1 CONT
1 CONT \----------
1 CONT
1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/NIKAIA.htm#MariaLaskarinadied1270>
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT 2\. **MARIA Laskarina** (-16 or 24 Jul 1270, bur Esztergom). Georgius
1 CONT Akropolites names "Irene, Maria et Eudocia" as the three daughters of
1 CONT "Theodorum Lascarim imperatorem…ex Anna uxore", stating that "Mariam secundam"
1 CONT married "Ungariæ regis…filio", his father arranging the marriage on his
1 CONT journey back from Jerusalem[59]. Ephræmius records that "Anna regina coniuge
1 CONT Lascario" had three daughters "Irene et Maria et Eudocia", recording that
1 CONT "Mariam…natu secundo" married "regis Paeoniæ filio"[60]. The Chronicle of
1 CONT Alberic de Trois-Fontaines records that "rex Bela, regis Andree filius
1 CONT primogenitus" married one of the daughters (mentioned third) of "Lascarum
1 CONT Grecum"[61]. The Historia Salonitanorum of Thomas Archdeacon of Split records
1 CONT that András II King of Hungary arranged the marriage of "suo filio primogenito
1 CONT Bele" and "Lascaro rege Grecorum…filiam eius" while he was in Greece[62]. The
1 CONT Annales Polonorum record the death in 1270 of "regina Ungarorum Maria, mater
1 CONT domine Kinge"[63]. The necrology of Oberaltaich records the death "IX Kal Aug"
1 CONT of "Maria regina Ungarie"[64]. The necrology of Seligenthal records the death
1 CONT "XVII Kal Aug" of "Maria regina Ungarie"[65]. The Altahenses Annales record
1 CONT that "Maria regina Ungarie" died after her husband "non post longum
1 CONT tempus"[66]. The Chronicon Dubnicense records that "consorte sua Maria…filia
1 CONT imperatoris Grecorum" was buried with her husband "rex Bela" in "Strigony in
1 CONT ecclesia fratrum minorum"[67].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** (1218) BÉLA of Hungary, son of ANDRÁS II King of Hungary & his first
1 CONT wife Gertrud von Andechs-Merano (Nov 1206-Margaret Island, near Buda 3 May
1 CONT 1270, bur Esztergom). He succeeded his father in 1235 as BÉLA IV King of
1 CONT Hungary.
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------
1 CONT
1 CONT -<http://genealogy.euweb.cz/byzant/byzant6.html>
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT ====The Laskaris family====
1 CONT
1 CONT One Manuel Laskaris, *ca 1140; m.Ioanna Karatzaina (*ca 1148) and had issue:*
1 CONT ...
1 CONT
1 CONT   * A5. Theodoros I Komnenos Laskaris, Emperor of Nicea (1205-22), *1175, +VIII.1222; 1m: 1199 Anna Komnena Angelina (*ca 1156 +1212); 2m: 1214 (div 1216) Philippa (*1183, +after 1219) dau.of Rupen III of Armenia, Lord of the Mountains; 3m: 1219 Ma
1 CONC rie de Courtenay (*1204 +IX.1222)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B1. [1m.] Nikolaos, +ca 1212
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B2. [1m.] Ioannes, +ca 1212
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B3. [1m.] Eirene Dukaina Komnene Laskarina, +1239; 1m: 1212 Konstantinos Dukas Palaiologos (+1212); 2m: ca 1212 Ioannes III Dukas Batatzes, Emp of Byzantium in Nicaea (*ca 1192 +Nymphaion 3.11.1254)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B4. [1m.] **Maria Laskarina, *Nicaea ca 1206, +1270** ; m.1218 King Bela IV of Hungary (*1206 +3.5.1270)
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B5. [1m.] Eudokia Laskarina; engaged to Robert de Courtenay; m.before 1230 Anseau de Cayeux, Gov of Asia Minor
1 CONT
1 CONT     * B6. [2m.] Konstantinos Laskaris, Duke of Thrace, *1214
1 CONT
1 CONT   * ...
1 CONT \--------
1 CONT \-------
