1 CONT Maria Laskarina
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT Maria Laskarina (c. 1206- July, 1270) was a daughter of Theodore I Laskaris
1 CONT and his first wife Anna Angelina.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit] Life
1 CONT She was a younger sister of Irene Lascarina, first Empress consort of John III
1 CONT Doukas Vatatzes. Theodore married his eldest daughter to his designated heir
1 CONT in 1212. Theodore was widowed in the same year and proceeded to marriages with
1 CONT Philippa of Armenia and Marie de Courtenay. However John was never displaced
1 CONT in succession.
1 CONT
1 CONT As a younger daughter, the marriage of Maria was not intended to add a
1 CONT potential husband in the line of succession to the throne. Instead it secured
1 CONT a marital alliance with the Kingdom of Hungary.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1218, Maria was married to prince Béla of Hungary. Bride and groom were
1 CONT about twelve-years-old. Her husband was the eldest son of Andrew II of Hungary
1 CONT and Gertrude of Merania.
1 CONT
1 CONT Andrew II died on 26 October 1235. The crown prince succeeded him as Béla IV
1 CONT and Maria became his Queen consort. Béla reigned for thirty-five years and
1 CONT died on 3 May 1270. Maria survived him by about two months.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit] Children
1 CONT Maria and Béla IV of Hungary had ten children:
1 CONT
1 CONT Margaret of Hungary (c. 1220 - 20 April 1242). Married Guillaume de Saint-
1 CONT Omer. Her husband is often listed in genealogies as "Lord of Thebes". However
1 CONT he might be confused with Bela de Saint-Omer, an older brother who held the
1 CONT the title jure uxoris.
1 CONT Kunegunda of Hungary (5 March 1224 - 24 July 1292), also known as Kinga. She
1 CONT was married to King Boleslaus V of Poland, after his death becoming a nun and
1 CONT abbess; she was canonized by Pope John Paul II in 1999.
1 CONT Anna of Hungary (c. 1226 - after 1270). Married Rostislav of Slavonia.
1 CONT Catherine of Hungary. (c. 1229 - 1242). She died while fleeing with her family
1 CONT following the Battle of Mohi.
1 CONT Elizabeth of Hungary (c. 1236 - 24 October 1271). Married Henry XIII, Duke of
1 CONT Bavaria.
1 CONT Constance of Hungary (c. 1237 - after 1252). Married Leo I of Halych.
1 CONT Yolanda of Hungary (c. 1238 - 1298). Married Boleslaus of Greater Poland.
1 CONT Later became a nun and abbess, who has been declared as a candidate for
1 CONT sainthoood.
1 CONT Stephen V of Hungary (December, 1239 - 6 August 1272).
1 CONT Saint Margaret of Hungary (27 January 1242 - 18 January 1271). Named after an
1 CONT older sister. Canonized by the Roman Catholic Church in 1943, for whom
1 CONT Margaret Island in Budapest is named, having been the place where a royal
1 CONT monastery was established by her parents for her.
1 CONT Béla, Duke of Slavonia, Croatia and Dalmatia (c. 1243 - 1269). Married
1 CONT Kunigunde of Brandenburg, a daughter of Otto III, Margrave of Brandenburg. His
1 CONT widow married Waleran IV of Limburg.
1 CONT Royal titles
1 CONT Preceded by
1 CONT Beatrice d'Este Queen consort of Hungary
1 CONT 1235-1270 Succeeded by
1 CONT Elizabeth the Cuman
