1 CONT daughter of Conrad of Montferrat and Isabella, Queen of Jerusalem. Her father
1 CONT was murdered on 28 April 1192 in Tyre by the Hashshashin. Her mother married
1 CONT Henry II of Champagne on 5 May, when already noticeably pregnant (The Old
1 CONT French Continuation of William of Tyre and Imad ad-Din al-Isfahani remarked on
1 CONT this). Maria was thus born posthumously.
1 CONT
1 CONT On her mother's death in 1205, Maria became Queen of Jerusalem, aged thirteen.
1 CONT Her mother's half-brother John of Ibelin, Lord of Beirut, acted as regent for
1 CONT Maria.
1 CONT
1 CONT On September 14, 1210, Maria married John of Brienne (c. 1150–1237) in Acre in
1 CONT an arranged marriage. Their daughter Yolande of Jerusalem (also known as
1 CONT Isabella) was born in 1212, but Maria died shortly after, probably from
1 CONT puerperal fever. John became regent for his daughter Yolande, now Queen of
1 CONT Jerusalem.
1 CONT
1 CONT Maria's line died out in 1268, when her great-grandson Conrad III of Jerusalem
1 CONT was executed in Southern Italy. After that, her next half-sister's (Alice of
1 CONT Champagne's) descendants became heirs-general of Queen Isabella of Jerusalem.
