1 CONT the prior of Saint-Victor the right to fortify the monastery by charter dated
1 CONT 1220[669]. m ---. The name of Humbert's wife is not known. Humbert & his wife
1 CONT had three children **Guillaume [I] & his second wife had four children:**
1 CONT
1 CONT 2\. **AIMON (1174-[1191/95]).** Willelmus…Gebennensis comes" founded the
1 CONT Chartreuse monstery of Pommiers, with the consent of "Humbertus filius meus…B.
1 CONT quoque uxor mea et filius meus Aymo quinquennis", by charter dated 1179[680].
1 CONT **3\. MARGUERITE [Beatrix] (-8 Apr 1257, bur Abbaye de Hautecombe).** The
1 CONT Chronicle of Alberic de Trois-Fontaines names "Margareta filia domni de
1 CONT Fusceneis de matre Guilelmi, filii Humberti comitis Gebenensis" as wife of
1 CONT "comitis Thome de Sabaudia"[681]. As noted below, Marguerite is also called
1 CONT Beatrix in later sources. No explanation has been found for these dual names.
1 CONT The fact that "Beatrix" appears in a seal shows that it was not a
1 CONT transcription error. "Thomæ comitis et marchionis…et…Nichola [presumably a
1 CONT transcription error] filia comitis Gebennarum" granted privileges to the
1 CONT citizen of Susa by charter dated 25 Feb 1198[682]. The Complete Peerage[683]
1 CONT refers to unspecified "later writers" who evolved an incorrect theory that
1 CONT Thomas I Comte de Maurienne was married firstly to Béatrix and, after her
1 CONT death without issue, secondly to Marguerite, daughter of Guillaume de
1 CONT Faucigny, who was the mother of his children. The same source confirms that
1 CONT the two names in fact refer to the same person. A charter dated 1224 records
1 CONT an agreement between "Thomæ com. Sabaud" and the bishop of Sion, witnessed by
1 CONT "ipse Thomas comes, Amedeus primogenitus illius, Comitissa uxor Thomæ, eorum
1 CONT quatuor filii clerici…Willelmus, Thomas, Petrus et Bonifacius"[684]. "M.
1 CONT comitissa Maurian. uxor Thomæ comitis Maurianensis et marchionis Italiæ"
1 CONT donated property, with the consent of "Thomas com. Maurianæ et filii mei
1 CONT Amedeus et Aymo", by charter dated Dec 1227[685]. "Beatrix uxor comitis Thomæ,
1 CONT Amadeus primogenitus et Aymo filii eius" confirmed the purchase of Chambéry by
1 CONT "Thoma comite" by charter dated 1232, with the seal of "Beatricis comitisse
1 CONT Sabaudie"[686]. "Contessa Margarita di Savoia Marchesa in Italia" donated
1 CONT property to "Tomaso suo figlio Conte di Fiandra e d'Hainaut" with the consent
1 CONT of "Conte Amedeo di Savoia suo figlio Primogenito", by charter dated 4 Jan
1 CONT 1244[687]. The Pingonio Chronicon records the death "VI Id Apr" in 1257 of
1 CONT "Domina Beatrix de Gebennis comitissa Sabaudie et domina de Narembors, parens
1 CONT comitum Sabaudie"[688]. m ([1196]) THOMAS I Comte de Savoie, son of HUMBERT
1 CONT III Comte de Maurienne et de Savoie & his fourth wife Béatrix de Vienne
1 CONT [Bourgogne-Comté] (Château de Carbonara 1178 after 26 Jun-Moncalieri 1 Mar
1 CONT 1233, bur Saint-Michel de la Cluse).
1 CONT
1 CONT 4\. **AMEDEE (-17 Dec [1220]). Bishop of Maurienne 1213.** "Willelmus comes
1 CONT Gebennensis" swore homage to the archbishop of Tarantasia for the valley of
1 CONT Hauteluce, with the consent of "dominus Amedeus…Maurianensis episcopus frater
1 CONT noster", by charter dated 30 Jul 1220[689]. A charter dated 12 Jan 1270
1 CONT records donations by Pierre Bishop of Maurienne to found anniversaries for his
1 CONT predecessors "dominus Amedeus Maurianensis episcopus frater quondam…Villelmi
1 CONT comitis Gebennensis…dominus Amedeus Maurianensis episcopus frater quondam
1 CONT domini Villelmi de Miribello"[690].
1 CONT
1 CONT 5\. **GUILLAUME [II] (-25 Nov 1252).** "Dominus Willelmus Gebenensis…frater
1 CONT Humberti comitis Gebenensis" issued letters of protection to Chamonix by
1 CONT charter dated 13 Mar 1205, naming "pater eius Willelmus comes Gebennensis bone
1 CONT memorie"[691]. Comte de Genève.
1 CONT
1 CONT William I of Geneva
1 CONT
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT William I of Geneva was Count of Geneva. In 1195 he was escorting his
1 CONT daughter, Marguerite of Geneva, to France for her intended wedding to King
1 CONT Philip II of France. Thomas I of Savoy ambushed the party and carried off
1 CONT Marguerite and married her himself, producing some eight sons and six
1 CONT daughters.
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------------
1 CONT His third marriage, to Beatrice de Vaupergue, was childless.
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit] Notes
1 CONT
1 CONT 1.^ In 1195 William was escorting his daughter Marguerite to France for her
1 CONT intended wedding to King Philip II. Thomas of Savoy ambushed the party,
1 CONT carried off Marguerite and married her himself, producing some eight sons and
1 CONT six daughters.
