1 CONT Amadeus IV of Savoy
1 CONT
1 CONT Amadeus IV (1197 – June 24 or July 13 1253) was Count of Savoy from 1233 to
1 CONT 1253.
1 CONT The legitimate heir of Thomas I of Savoy and Marguerite of Geneva, he had
1 CONT however to fight with his brothers for the inheritance of Savoy lands after
1 CONT their father's death. His brothers Pietro and Aimone spurred a revolt in Aosta
1 CONT Valley against Amadeus, but he was able to crush it with the help of Manfred
1 CONT III of Saluzzo and Boniface II of Montferrat, who were his sons-in-law.
1 CONT Together with his brother Thomas, he fought against the communes of Turin and
1 CONT Pinerolo, but with uncertain results.
1 CONT He was succeeded by his young son Boniface, who died soon.
1 CONT
1 CONT Family and children
1 CONT He married twice:
1 CONT 1\. Anne of Burgundy, daughter of Hugh III, Duke of Burgundy.
1 CONT 1\. Beatrice of Savoy (d. 1258), married firstly in 1233 Manfred, Margrave of
1 CONT Saluzzo (d. 1244), married secondly on April 21, 1247 Manfred of Sicily
1 CONT 2\. Margaret of Savoy (d. 1254), married firstly on December 9, 1235 Boniface
1 CONT II of Montferrat, married secondly Aymar III, Count of Valentinois
1 CONT 1\. Cecilia of Baux, "Passerose", daughter of Barral of Baux
1 CONT 1\. Boniface of Savoy
1 CONT 2\. Beatrice of Savoy (1250 – February 23, 1292) married Peter of Chalon and
1 CONT Juan Manuel of Castile.
1 CONT 3\. Eleonor of Savoy, married in 1269 Guichard de Beaujeu
1 CONT 4\. Constance of Savoy, died after 1263
1 CONT
1 CONT Preceded by Thomas I
1 CONT Count of Savoy 1233–1253
1 CONT Succeeded by Boniface and Thomas II
1 CONT Children
1 CONT 1\. Beatrice de Savoy b: ABT 1215 in Savoy, France
1 CONT 2\. Marguerite de Savoy b: ABT 1215 in Savoy, France
