1 CONT Humbert III, the Count of Savoy
1 CONT [http://trees.ancestry.com/rd?f=image&guid=a39d0dcd-8122-4b0d-919b-2a4a8769bc00&tid=5698773&pid=-1248778217](http://trees.ancestry.com/rd?f=image&guid=a39d0dcd-8122-4b0d-919b-2a4a8769bc00&tid=5698773&pid=-1248778217)
1 CONT Humbert III (1135-1189), surnamed the Blessed, was Count of Savoy from 1148 to
1 CONT 1189. His parents were Amadeus III of Savoy and Mahaut (or Mafalda, or
1 CONT Matilda) of Albon, the sister of Guy IV of Dauphinois. His memorial day is
1 CONT March 4.
1 CONT
1 CONT According to Cope[1]
1 CONT
1 CONT Humbert III, who reigned from 1149 to 1189...was a man of irresolute spirit
1 CONT who was disconsolate at being born a prince and preferred the seclusion of a
1 CONT monastery. He only renounced his chosen state of celibacy so as to give his
1 CONT land an heir.
1 CONT
1 CONT His first wife died young; his second marriage ended in divorce. Humbert gave
1 CONT up and became a Carthusian monk. However, the nobles and common people of
1 CONT Savoy begged him to marry yet again, which he reluctantly did. This third wife
1 CONT gave him two more daughters, and Humbert attempted to return to the monastic
1 CONT life yet again. Finally he was prevailed upon to marry for a fourth time, and
1 CONT this wife, Beatrice, produced the son who would ultimately succeed him.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1188 he founded the Monastery of Sant'Antonio di Ranverso.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT Family
1 CONT Humbert married four times:
1 CONT
1 CONT Faidiva (Italian) (d. abt 1154) daughter of Alphonse I of Toulouse
1 CONT Gertrude of Flanders (m. abt 1155), whom he divorced and confined. She was
1 CONT freed thanks to Robert, bishop of Cambrai and returned to the court of her
1 CONT brother, Philip of Flanders
1 CONT Clemenza of Zähringen (married 1164), daughter of Conrad I of Zähringen.
1 CONT They had 2 daughters:
1 CONT Sofia, (1165-1202), married Azzo VI of Este
1 CONT Alicia, (1166-1178), betrothed to John of England
1 CONT Beatrice of Viennois and had 1 son:
1 CONT Tommaso (born 1178)
