1 CONT Humbert III (1135–1189), surnamed the Blessed, was Count of Savoy from 1148 to
1 CONT 1189. His parents were Amadeus III of Savoy and Mahaut (or Mafalda, or
1 CONT Matilda) of Albon, the sister of Guy IV of Dauphinois. His memorial day is
1 CONT March 4.
1 CONT According to Cope[1], "Humbert III, who reigned from 1149 to 1189...was a man
1 CONT of irresolute spirit who was disconsolate at being born a prince and preferred
1 CONT the seclusion of a monastery. He only renounced his chosen state of celibacy
1 CONT so as to give his land an heir."
1 CONT His first wife died young; his second marriage ended in divorce. Humbert gave
1 CONT up and became a Carthusian monk. However, the nobles and common people of
1 CONT Savoy begged him to marry yet again, which he reluctantly did. This third wife
1 CONT gave him two more daughters, and Humbert attempted to return to the monastic
1 CONT life yet again. Finally he was prevailed upon to marry for a fourth time, and
1 CONT this wife, Beatrice, produced the son who would ultimately succeed him.
1 CONT
1 CONT He married four times
1 CONT • Faidiva (Italian) (d. abt 1154) daughter of Alphonse I of Toulouse
1 CONT • Gertrude of Flanders (m. abt 1155), whom he divorced and confined. She was
1 CONT freed thanks to Robert, bishop of Cambrai and returned to the court of her
1 CONT brother, Philip of Flanders
1 CONT • Clemenza of Zähringen (married 1164), daughter of Conrad I of Zähringen.
1 CONT They had 2 daughters:
1 CONT • Sofia, (1165-1202), married Azzo IV of Este
1 CONT • Alicia, (1166-1178), betrothed to John of England
1 CONT • Beatrice of Viennois and had 1 son:
1 CONT • Tommaso (born 1178)
1 CONT
1 CONT External links
1 CONT • Humbert at Patron Saints Index
1 CONT
1 CONT References
1 CONT 1\. ^ Cope, Christopher. The Lost Kingdom of Burgundy
1 CONT
1 CONT Preceded by Amadeus III
1 CONT Count of Savoy
1 CONT Succeeded by Thomas I
1 CONT FROM LEO VAN DE PAS:
1 CONT
1 CONT BIOGRAPHY
1 CONT
1 CONT Umberto, known as 'the Blessed', was born on 1 August 1136, the son of Amadeo
1 CONT III, Comte de Savoie, and Mathilde d'Albon. In 1148, when only twelve years
1 CONT old, he succeeded his father as Count of Savoy.
1 CONT
1 CONT According to Christopher Cope (_The Lost Kingdom of Burgundy_), 'Humbert III,
1 CONT who reigned from 1148 to 1189, was a man of irresolute spirit who was
1 CONT disconsolate at being born a prince and preferred the seclusion of a
1 CONT monastery. He only renounced his chosen state of celibacy so as to give his
1 CONT land an heir'.
1 CONT
1 CONT Before 3 January 1151 he married Faydiva whose origins are unknown. Faydiva
1 CONT died about 1154 and a year later he married Gertrud of Flanders. Umberto
1 CONT confined Gertrud for reasons unknown, but she was rescued by a cleric from
1 CONT Flanders, Robert, provost of Arie, who profited from his efforts through the
1 CONT high regard of her brother and later became bishop-elect of Cambrai. However
1 CONT on 4 October 1174, while still not consecrated, he was murdered at the behest
1 CONT of Jacques d'Avesnes.
1 CONT
1 CONT Before 1162 Umberto III and Gertrud were divorced. At this point he gave up
1 CONT his attempts at parenthood and became a Carthusian monk. However, the nobles
1 CONT and common people of Savoy begged him to marry yet again, which he reluctantly
1 CONT did.
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1164 he married Klementia von Zähringen and they became the parents of two
1 CONT daughters, whereupon Umberto attempted to return to the monastic life yet
1 CONT again. Klementia died between 1173 and 1175, and he was prevailed upon to
1 CONT marry for a fourth time. About 1175 he married Beatrice de Maçon and by her
1 CONT fathered his son and heir, Thomas. When Umberto III died on 4 March 1189, his
1 CONT son was not quite twelve.
1 CONT
1 CONT \----------------
1 CONT
1 CONT Marriage 1 Faydiva b: ABT 1136 in France
1 CONT • Married: 3 JAN 1150/51 in 1st wife 1
1 CONT
1 CONT Marriage 2 Gertrude of Flanders b: ABT 1140 in Alsace & Lorraine, France
1 CONT • Married: 1155 in 2nd wife - divorced bef. 1162 1
1 CONT
1 CONT Marriage 3 Klementia von Zahringen b: ABT 1140 in Zahringen, Germany
1 CONT • Married: 1164 in 3rd wife 1
1 CONT Children
1 CONT 1\. Sofie de Savoy b: ABT 1165 in Savoy, France
1 CONT
1 CONT Marriage 4 Beatrice de Macon b: ABT 1161 in Macon, Saone-et-Loire, Bourgogne,
1 CONT France
1 CONT • Married: 1175 in 4th wife 1
1 CONT Children
1 CONT 1\. Thomas (Tomaso) I Count of Savoy b: 20 MAR 1176/77 in Carbonierres-les-
1 CONT Bains, Rhone, Rhone-Alpes, France
