0 @N00778@ NOTE geni:about_me
1 CONT
1 CONT ==Marguerite of Burgundy, Countess of Savoy==
1 CONT
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marguerite_of_Burgundy,_Countess_of_Savoy>
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Born 1192
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Died 1243
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Noble family House of Burgundy
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Spouse(s) Amadeus IV, Count of Savoy
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Father Hugh III, Duke of Burgundy
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Mother Béatrice of Albon
1 CONT
1 CONT Marguerite of Burgundy (referred to as Anne by some sources; 1192–1243), was,
1 CONT by marriage, Countess of Savoy from 1233 until her death. She was the youngest
1 CONT daughter of Hugh III, Duke of Burgundy, and his second wife, Béatrice of
1 CONT Albon.
1 CONT
1 CONT Around 1217, she married Amadeus IV, Count of Savoy. As dowry, she brought
1 CONT Miribel castle, Ornacieux castle, and other properties in Viennois territory.
1 CONT The marriage was agreed to as part of a treaty between the families, including
1 CONT terms not to acquire further territories within each other's dominions. She
1 CONT and her new husband were also designated as heirs for her brother Guigues VI
1 CONT of Viennois after any children of his.[1] However, this peace between the
1 CONT families did not last long, with conflict resuming by 1228.[2]
1 CONT
1 CONT She also personally inherited some money upon the death of her mother. The
1 CONT 1267 will of her nephew Guigues VII of Viennois confirmed donations of
1 CONT property which she had made.
1 CONT
1 CONT Marguerite and Amadeus had two daughters:
1 CONT
1 CONT Beatrice of Savoy (d. 1258), married firstly in 1233 to Manfred III of Saluzzo
1 CONT (d. 1244), married secondly on April 21, 1247 to Manfred of Sicily
1 CONT
1 CONT Margaret of Savoy (d. 1254), married firstly on December 9, 1235 to Boniface
1 CONT II of Montferrat, married secondly to Aymar III, Count of Valentinois
1 CONT
1 CONT Note that some scholars are unclear on Marguerite's given name. A book about
1 CONT the house of Savoy at this time mentions the debate regarding her name,[1] but
1 CONT finds a source[3] which Cox finds settles the debate.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT ===Notes===
1 CONT
