0 @N00786@ NOTE geni:about_me *<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beatrice_of_Viennois>
1 CONT
1 CONT Beatrice was born in 1160 in Vienne, France, the second child of Géraud I of
1 CONT Mâcon (son of William III of Mâcon) and Maurette de Salins. She was descended
1 CONT from the House of Mâcon and had seven siblings.
1 CONT
1 CONT After the death of Humbert III, Count of Savoy's third wife, Clementia of
1 CONT Zähringen, in 1175, Humbert was inconsolable and refused to remarry; however,
1 CONT he had no male heir. His advisers persuaded him to wed Beatrice the following
1 CONT year.[1] Beatrice gave birth to Thomas, Count of Savoy in 1178.[2]
1 CONT
1 CONT Beatrice died in 1230 in Champagne-et-Fontaine, Aquitaine, France.
1 CONT
1 CONT \-----------
1 CONT
1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/BURGUNDIAN%20NOBILITY.htm#BeatrixMacondied1230>
1 CONT
1 CONT 6\. BEATRIX de Vienne (-8 Apr 1230). The Chronicle of Alberic de Trois-
1 CONT Fontaines refers to one of the unnamed sisters of "comitem Guilelmum
1 CONT Matisconensem sive Viennensem et Galterum de Salins et quemdam Gerardum et
1 CONT Stephanum Bisuntinensem electum" as mother of "comes Thomas de Sabaudia"[256].
1 CONT The primary source which confirms her name has not been identified.
1 CONT "Thomas…Mauriannensis comes et marchio Italiæ" confirmed the donations made by
1 CONT "pater meus…[et] domini comitis Humberti…abavi mei" to the canons of Saint-
1 CONT Jean de Maurienne, with the advice of "B. matris mee et…tutore meo Bonifacio
1 CONT marchione Montisferrati", by charter dated 12 Jun 1189[257]. The necrology of
1 CONT Hautecombe records the death of "Beatrix comitissa" 8 Apr 1230[258].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** ([1175]) as his fourth wife, HUMBERT III Comte de Maurienne et de
1 CONT Savoie, son of AMEDEE III Comte de Maurienne et de Savoie & his wife Mathilde
1 CONT d'Albon [Viennois] (Avigliana 4 Aug 1136-Chambéry 4 Mar 1189, bur Abbaye de
1 CONT Hautecombe).
1 CONT
