1 CONT
1 CONT Érard II of Brienne († 1191) was count of Brienne from 1161 to 1191, and a
1 CONT French general during the Third Crusade, most notably at the Siege of Acre. He
1 CONT was the son of Gautier II, count of Brienne, and of Adèle of Soissons. During
1 CONT this siege he saw his brother André of Brienne die on 4 October 1189 before
1 CONT being killed himself on 8 February 1191. Erard II's nephew was Erard of
1 CONT Brienne-Ramerupt.
1 CONT
1 CONT Before 1166 he married Agnès of Montfaucon († after 1186), daughter of Amadeus
1 CONT II of Montfaucon and of Béatrice of Grandson-Joinville. Their children were:
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Gautier III of Brienne († 1205) count of Brienne and claimant to the throne of Sicily.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * William of Brienne († 1199) lord of Pacy-sur-Armançon, married Eustachie of Courtenay, daughter of Pierre de France and of Elisabeth of Courtenay.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * André of Brienne († after 1181)
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * John of Brienne (1170 † 1237), king of Jerusalem (1210-1225), then emperor of Constantinople (1231-1237).
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Ida of Brienne who married Arnoul of Reynel lord of Pierrefitte.
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------------
1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/chambrien.htm#ErardBriennedied1190B>
1 CONT
1 CONT ERARD [II] de Brienne, son of GAUTHIER [II] Seigneur de Brienne & his
1 CONT [first/second] wife Humbeline de Baudément (-8 Feb [1190/91]). "Walterus
1 CONT Brenensis comes" granted "decimam reddituum suorum de Brena Castello" to the
1 CONT abbey of Basse-Fontaine by charter dated 22 Jan 1143, subscribed by "Airardi
1 CONT filii sui, Andree filii sui, Marie filie sue…Johannis de Brena
1 CONT clerici…Guidonis fratris comitis"[86]. "G comes Brene" donated property to
1 CONT "ecclesie Sancte Marie de Rameruco" with the consent of "uxoris Adelisis,
1 CONT Erardi, Andreæ filium meorum atque Marie filie mee" by charter dated 1147[87].
1 CONT He succeeded his father in [1161] as Comte de Brienne. "Erardus Brenensis
1 CONT comes", recalling "bone memorie Galteri comitis…Brenensis", donated property
1 CONT to the abbey of Basse-Fontaine in the presence of "matris mee et Johannis
1 CONT fratris mei abbatis Belliloci et domini Willermi de Dompetra" and with the
1 CONT consent of "Agnetis uxoris mee et Andree fratris mee" by charter dated
1 CONT 1166[88]. He took part in the Fourth Crusade in 1189[89].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** (before 1166) AGNES de Montbéliard, daughter of AMEDEE de Montfaucon
1 CONT Comte de Montbéliard & his first wife Beatrix --- ([1150/55]-23 Oct ---, after
1 CONT 1186). "Agnetis uxoris mee" consented to the donation by "Erardus Brenensis
1 CONT comes" recorded in the latter's charter dated 1166[90]. The primary source
1 CONT which confirms her parentage has not yet been identified. "Erardus comes
1 CONT Brenensis…comitissa uxore mea Agnete, filiis quoque meis Galtero…et Guillelmo
1 CONT et Andrea" made a donation to Montiérender by charter dated 1181[91]. "Erardus
1 CONT Brenensium comes…Agnetis uxoris mee et Galterii filii mei" donated property to
1 CONT Basse-Fontaine by charter dated 1185[92]. "Erardus Brenensium comes" donated
1 CONT property to Basse-Fontaine with the consent of "Agnetis uxoris mee et Galteri
1 CONT et Guillelmi filiorum meorum" by charter dated 1186, witnessed by "Johannes
1 CONT frater meus abbas Belliloci…Andreas frater meus"[93]. The necrology of
1 CONT Chartres cathedral records the death "X Kal Nov" of "Agnes…comitissa de
1 CONT Breina"[94].
1 CONT
1 CONT Comte Erard [II] & his wife had five children:
1 CONT
1 CONT \-------
1 CONT \-------
1 CONT \------
1 CONT
