1 CONT -<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/burgkmontb.htm#AgnesMonfauconMErardIIBrienne>
1 CONT
1 CONT 1\. AGNES de Montbéliard ([1150/55]-23 Oct ---, after 1186). Her parentage is
1 CONT indicated by William of Tyre (Continuator), who names "le conte Gautier de
1 CONT Briene qui fu fiz dou conte Erart de Brienne et de la fille dou conte Ami de
1 CONT Monbliart" and says that “Rechart le conte de Monbliart et Gautier son frere
1 CONT furent ses oncles de par sa mere”[28]. If that is correct, the chronology of
1 CONT her husband’s family suggests that Agnes was much older than her brothers.
1 CONT "Agnetis uxoris mee" consented to the donation by "Erardus Brenensis comes"
1 CONT recorded in the latter's charter dated 1166[29]. The date of this charter
1 CONT suggests that Agnes must have been one of her parents’s older children to have
1 CONT been married before that time. Her birth date range is estimated from the
1 CONT birth of her fourth son which is estimated to [1170/75]. This in turn suggests
1 CONT that she was not born from the same marriage as her brother Richard [III].
1 CONT "Erardus Brenensium comes…Agnetis uxoris mee et Galterii filii mei" donated
1 CONT property to Basse-Fontaine by charter dated 1185[30]. "Erardus Brenensium
1 CONT comes" donated property to Basse-Fontaine with the consent of "Agnetis uxoris
1 CONT mee et Galteri et Guillelmi filiorum meorum" by charter dated 1186[31]. The
1 CONT necrology of Chartres cathedral records the death "X Kal Nov" of
1 CONT "Agnes…comitissa de Breina"[32].
1 CONT
1 CONT **m** (before 1166) ERARD [II] Comte de Brienne, son of GAUTHIER [II] Comte de
1 CONT Brienne & his [first/second] wife Humbeline de Baudément (-8 Feb [1190/91]).
1 CONT
1 CONT \--------- Agnes de Montfaucon1
1 CONT
1 CONT F, #120026
1 CONT
1 CONT Last Edited=1 May 2004
1 CONT
