1 CONT Boleslaw II the Bald
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT Boleslaw II the Bald the Tollgate (Polish: Boleslaw II Lysy Rogatka) (1220/5 -
1 CONT December 26, 1278) was the eldest son of Henryk II the Pious.
1 CONT
1 CONT After his father's death, he became Duke of central Greater Poland (1241 -
1 CONT 1247) and Duke of Silesia (1241 -1248). After the partiton of Silesia, he was
1 CONT Duke of Legnica - Glogów. He lost Lubusz and Glogów in 1249. During his rule
1 CONT there was a second mongol raid against Poland, led by Nogai Khan. He was Duke
1 CONT of Sroda Slaska from 1277.
1 CONT This biography of a Polish noble is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by
1 CONT expanding it.
1 CONT This biography of a member of a European royal house is a stub. You can help
1 CONT Wikipedia by expanding it.
1 CONT Preceded by:
1 CONT Henryk II the Pious Duke of Wroclaw Succeeded by:
1 CONT Henryk III the White
1 CONT Wladyslaw of Salzburg
