0 @N00832@ NOTE geni:about_me =Agnes von der Pfalz Wittelsbach=
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Also known as Duchess Agnes of Wittelsbach
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Daughter of Henry V "the elder" Guelph, Count Palatine of the Rhine and Agnes von Hohenstaufen.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT ==[<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/PALATINATE.htm#Agnesdied1267> Project
1 CONT MedLands, PALATINATE]
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT **HEINRICH von Sachsen, son of HEINRICH "der Löwe" ex-Duke of Saxony and
1 CONT Bavaria [Welf] & his second wife Matilda of England ([1173/74]-Braunschweig 28
1 CONT Apr 1227, bur Braunschweig Cathedral).** The Chronicon Montis Serreni names
1 CONT (in order) "Heinricum comitem Palatinum Reni, Othonem imperatorem, Willehelmus
1 CONT de Luneburch, Luderum" as children of "Heinricus dux de Bruneswich" & his wife
1 CONT "soror Rikardi regis Anglie"[36]. He accompanied his parents to England in
1 CONT 1182[37]. Vogt of Gotzlar 1204. He campaigned with Heinrich VI King of Germany
1 CONT in Italy in 1190, but deserted in southern Italy and was outlawed at Worms in
1 CONT May 1192[38]. He was restored to favour by the Emperor in Jan 1194 at Würzburg
1 CONT following his marriage[39]. He succeeded in 1195 as HEINRICH I Pfalzgraf bei
1 CONT Rhein. He was deposed in 1212. Herzog von Braunschweig-Lüneburg 1213. The
1 CONT Libro Memoriarum Sancti Blasii records the death in Apr 1227 of "Hinricus dux
1 CONT Saxonie et comes palatine Reni"[40]. The Chronicon Sancti Michaelis
1 CONT Luneburgensis records that "Heinricum…palatinum Reni" was buried "Bruneswic…in
1 CONT ecclesie beati Blasii"[41]. **married firstly (Burg Stahleck [Dec 1193/Jan
1 CONT 1194]) AGNES von Staufen, daughter of KONRAD von Staufen Pfalzgraf bei Rhein &
1 CONT his second wife Irmgard von Henneberg (1176-Stade 9/10 May 1204, bur Stade St
1 CONT Marien).** The Chronicon Sancti Michaelis Luneburgensis names "filiam Conradi
1 CONT palatini fratris Friderici imperatoris, Agnetam" as wife of
1 CONT "Heinricum…palatinum Reni", specifying that she was buried "in ecclesie beate
1 CONT Virginis apud Stadium"[42]. Heiress of the Pfalzgrafschaft. Her marriage was
1 CONT arranged by her mother who wanted to avoid a marriage with Philippe II King of
1 CONT France[43]. Although opposed by her cousin Emperor Heinrich VI, it presented
1 CONT an opportunity for a reconciliation between the Welf and Staufen families[44].
1 CONT The Annales Stadenses records the death of "Agnes uxor Heinrici ducis et
1 CONT palatini comitis" and her burial "in ecclesia beatæ Virginis apud
1 CONT Stadium"[45]. The necrology of Seligenthal records the death "VI Id Mai" of
1 CONT "Agnes palatina Reni"[46]. **married secondly (1211) AGNES von Wettin,
1 CONT daughter of KONRAD von Landsberg Graf von Groitzsch und Sommerschenburg
1 CONT [Wettin] & his wife Elžbieta of Poland (-1 Jan 1248, bur Wienhausen).** The
1 CONT Genealogica Wettinensis names "Machtildem…et Agnetem" as the two daughters of
1 CONT "Conradus marchio filius Dedonis" & his wife, specifying that Agnes married
1 CONT "Heinricus palatinus Reni frater Othonis imperatoris"[47].
1 CONT
1 CONT **Heinrich I & his first wife AGNES von Staufen had three children:**
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * 1\. **HEINRICH** ([1196]-25 Apr 1214, bur Kloster Schönau bei Heidelberg). The Chronicon Sancti Michaelis Luneburgensis names "Henricum" as son of "Heinricum…palatinum Reni" & his wife, specifying that he died poisoned[48]. **He succeeded his f
1 CONC ather in 1212 as HEINRICH II Pfalzgraf bei Rhein.** The necrology of Seligenthal records the death "VII Kal Mai" of "Heinricus iunior palatinus"[49]. **married (Aachen end-Nov 1212) as her first husband, MATHILDE de Brabant, daughter of HENRI I "le
1 CONC  Guerroyeur" Duke of Brabant & his first wife Mathilde de Flandre (-22 Dec 1267, bur Loosduinen Cistercian Abbey).** The Oude Kronik van Brabant names "Mariam, conthoralem Ottonis Quartus Romanorum imperatoris, Aleydam comitssam Auernie, Margaretam
1 CONC  comitissam Gerardi comitis Ghelrie et Mechteldim, primo quidem comitissam Palatinam Rheni, postea…comitissam Hollandie" as the daughters of "Henricus…primus, dux Lotharingie" and his wife "Mechteldim, filiam Mathei Boloniensis comitis"[50]. The Ge
1 CONC nealogia Ducum Brabantiæ Heredum Franciæ names "Machtildem [uxor] Florentius comes Hollandie" as the fourth of the four daughters of "Henricus dux" & his wife Mathilde[51]. The Chronologia Johannes de Beke records the marriage of Count Floris IV an
1 CONC d "Machtildim filiam Henrici ducis Brabancie"[52]. She married secondly (5 Dec 1214) Floris IV Count of Holland. The Chronologia Johannes de Beke records the death "1267 VI Kal Ian" of "Machtildis comitissa" and her burial "apud puellæ cystersiensi
1 CONC s ordinis Losdunensis monasterii"[53].
1 CONT
1 CONT   * 2\. **IRMGARD** ([1200]-Lichtenthal 24 Feb 1260, bur Kloster Lichtental). The Annales Stadenses records the betrothal in Hamburg in 1202 of "duci Danorum" and "filiam fratris sui [=regis Otto] Heinrici"[54]. Although the daughter in question is
1 CONC  not named, it is probable that it was the older daughter Irmgard. The Altahenses Annales name "Iringarde sorore domine Agnetis ducisse Bawarie" as mother of "Hermannus marchio de Baden"[55]. The Genealogia Ottonis II Ducis Bavariæ names "Heinricus
1 CONC …comes palatinus Rheni…alteram filiam…Yrngardam" as wife of "Hermannus marchio de Baden"[56]. "Irmengardis relicta Hermanni Marchioni de Baden, soror ducissæ Bavaricæ" founded Kloster Lichtenthal in 1245, confirmed in 1246 by "Irmengardis marchioni
1 CONC ssa cum duobus filiis suis marchionibus…Hermanno et Rudolpho"[57]. The Chronicle of Lichtenthal records the donation of land "in Sunnesheim" made for the anniversary of "marchionis antiqui Hermanni et piæ memoriæ domnæ marchionissæ uxoris eius Irmi
1 CONC ngardis, fundatricis claustri hujus, et filii eius…ducis Austriæ Hermanni"[58]. Betrothed (Hamburg 1202) to VALDEMAR II "Sejr/the Conqueror" King of Denmark, son of VALDEMAR I "den Store/the Great" King of Denmark & his wife Sofia --- ([28 Jun] 117
1 CONC 0-Vordingborg 28 Mar 1241, bur Ringsted Church). **married ([1217]) HERMANN V Markgraf von Baden, son of HERMANN IV Markgraf von Baden & his wife Udalhildis --- (-15/16 Jan 1243, bur Backnang, transferred 1248 to Kloster Lichtental).**
1 CONT
1 CONT   * 3\. **AGNES** ([1201]-16 Nov 1267, bur Scheyern). The Notæ Sancti Emeranni record the marriage of "Otto dux Bawarie" and "filiam Heinrici palatine Rheni"[59]. The Altahenses Annales name "Agnes ducissa Bawarie" when recording the birth of her s
1 CONC on Ludwig[60]. The necrology of Fürstenfeld records the death "XVI Kal Dec" of "Agnes ducissa mater fundatoris nostri"[61]. The necrology of Weltenburg records the death "XVI Kal Dec" of "Agnnes ducissa Wabarie"[62]. The necrology of Seligenthal re
1 CONC cords the death "XVI Kal Nov" of "Agnetis coma palatina Reni ducissa Bawarie"[63]. **married (Worms May 1222) OTTO von Bayern, son of LUDWIG I Duke of Bavaria, Pfalzgraf bei Rhein & his wife Ludmila of Bohemia (Kelheim 1206-Landshut 29 Nov 1253, bu
1 CONC r Scheyern).** Pfalzgraf bei Rhein 1228. **He succeeded his father in 1231 as OTTO II "der Erlauchte" Duke of Bavaria.**
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT
