1 CONT Henry II the Pious
1 CONT From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
1 CONT
1 CONT Henry II the Pious (Polish: Henryk II Pobozny; German Heinrich II der Fromme;
1 CONT 1196/1207 - April 9, 1241) of Silesia was the third son of Henryk I the
1 CONT Bearded and of Hedwig of Andechs.
1 CONT
1 CONT Henry the Pious succeeded his father in 1238 and became the most powerful of
1 CONT all the Polish dukes. He united the majority of Polish territories (Silesia,
1 CONT Greater Poland and Little Poland).
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1239, Henry the Pious supported the Pope in the latter's conflict with
1 CONT Emperor Frederick II.
1 CONT
1 CONT Henry the Pious, the father of Henryk III the White, was able to defend his
1 CONT territories against Brandenburg.
1 CONT
1 CONT He was killed fighting the Mongols at the Battle of Legnica (1241).
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit]
1 CONT See also
1 CONT History of Poland (966-1385)
