0 @N00847@ NOTE geni:about_me The Hohenstaufen dynasty, or at least their name, became extinct
1 CONT with Corradino di Svevia, duke of the homonymous region, and the kings of
1 CONT Sicily and Jerusalem. The only son of Corrado IV and Elisabetta di Baviera, as
1 CONT Federico II became a very young king, when his father died when he was only
1 CONT two years old. Enemy of Charles of Anjou, he was defeated in 1268 by the
1 CONT latter, and beheaded after his capture in October of the same year.
1 CONT
1 CONT The last ruler of the Hohenstaufen had only one daughter, **Attilda von
1 CONT Hohenstaufen** , who was given in marriage to the baron of Frasano and
1 CONT Brienne, Milite Pietro Luca de Perregrino, to whom he gave a son, Giacomo.
1 CONT
1 CONT The surname became extinct, but the house of the dukes of Sveva can boast many
1 CONT learners, scattered throughout the European courts, thanks to the marriages of
1 CONT the female heirs.
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT ===Disputed Origins
1 CONT
1 CONT The source (below) names her Attilda, natural daughter of Corrado Sveva.
1 CONT
1 CONT Seen as daughter of <https://www.geni.com/people/Conrad-von-Hohenstaufen-Duke-
1 CONT of-Swabia-King-of-Jerusalem-and-
1 CONT Sicily/6000000000350865415?through=6000000032458416086>. On line trees for the
1 CONT House of Hohenstaufen place her as daughter of his half brother,
1 CONT <https://www.geni.com/people/Konradin-von-
1 CONT Sueva/6000000173175723954?through=6000000002244391295> by a woman called
1 CONT Margarita di San Lorenzo. The legitimate Conrad died at age 16 and the out of
1 CONT wedlock Conrad was aged 17 at death. Neither are known to have had children,
1 CONT and the Hohenstaufen dynasty ended in 1258.
1 CONT
