1 CONT
1 CONT == Heinrich I der Fette von Anhalt-Zerbst, Fürst zu Anhalt==
1 CONT
1 CONT **Totally different maternal line given
1 CONT here:<https://pl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jadwiga_anhalcka>**
1 CONT
1 CONT [http://finnholbek.dk/getperson.php?personID=I12433&tree=2](http://finnholbek.dk/getperson.php?personID=I12433&tree=2)
1 CONT
1 CONT **HEINRICH von Ballenstedt, son of BERNHARD von Ballenstedt Duke of Saxony,
1 CONT Graf von Aschersleben und Anhalt & his wife Judyta of Poland ([1170]-[8 May
1 CONT 1251/17 May 1252], bur Ballenstedt).** The Cronica Principum Saxonie names (in
1 CONT order) "Albertum ducem Saxonie et Henricum comitem de Anahalt et Magonem" as
1 CONT sons of "Bernardus dux Saxonie" & his wife[11]. He succeeded his father in
1 CONT 1212 as HEINRICH I "der Fette" Graf von Anhalt, Graf von Askarie, Graf von
1 CONT Aschersleben, the title Duke of Saxony passing to his younger brother. Vogt of
1 CONT Kloster Nienburg until 1220. "…Heinricus dux de Anhalt…" witnessed the charter
1 CONT dated 21 Feb 1219 under which Emperor Friedrich II confirmed an exchange of
1 CONT property involving Kloster Eberbach[12]. "…Heinricus comes de Anehalt,
1 CONT Albertus frater eius dux de Berneburch, filii ducis Bernhardi…" witnessed the
1 CONT charter dated [22/27] Jul [1220] under which Emperor Friedrich II granted
1 CONT protection to Kloster Lausnitz[13]. He was appointed tutor for Johann I and
1 CONT Otto III joint Markgrafen von Brandenburg in 1220, after the death of their
1 CONT father Markgraf Albrecht II: "Mechtildis…marchionissa Brandenburgensis,
1 CONT Johannes et Otto filii eius" purchased territories from the archbishop of
1 CONT Magdeburg, with the consent of "Henricus comes Ascharie, qui tutelam
1 CONT prefatorum nepotum nostrorum gerimus", by charter dated 20 Sep 1221[14].
1 CONT "Heynricus comes in Aschersleve" freed the church of Zernitz from the church
1 CONT at Bernburg by charter dated [Jan/Sep] 1228[15]. "Henricus…comes Ascharie"
1 CONT confirmed property of Kloster Nienburg, with the consent of "filiis nostris,
1 CONT Henrico…et Bernardo", by charter dated 1240[16]. The date of his death is set
1 CONT by the charter dated 17 May 1252 under which "Bernardus et Sifridus…comites
1 CONT Ascharie et principes de Anehalt…Hermannus Halberstadensis et Magnus
1 CONT Lubucensis prepositi, fratres eorundem" confirmed the donation by "patris
1 CONT nostri bone memorie" to Coswig[17 Codex Diplomaticus Anhaltinus, Teil II, 196,
1 CONT p. 151.]. [<http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/ANHALT.htm#_Toc359919196>
1 CONT Medlands]
1 CONT
1 CONT von Sachsen:
1 CONT
