1 CONT Count Palatine of the Rhine
1 CONT
1 CONT Henry (born 1175, died 28 April 1227) was count palatine of the Rhine from 6
1 CONT August 1195 to 1213.
1 CONT
1 CONT Henry was the eldest son of Duke Henry the Lion, from his marriage to Matilda
1 CONT of England. He grew up in England and became count palatine of the Rhine
1 CONT through his 1193 marriage to Agnes, heir to the Staufen count. When his
1 CONT younger brother Otto became one of two rival kings of the Holy Roman Empire in
1 CONT 1198, Henry at first supported him, but switched sides to Philip of Staufen in
1 CONT 1203. After he inherited significant properties in northern Germany from his
1 CONT brother William in 1213, he ceded the palatinate to his son Henry, and moved
1 CONT north. He left his northern German properties to William's son, Otto. Henry
1 CONT died in 1227 and is entombed in Brunswick Cathedral.
1 CONT
1 CONT [edit] Family
1 CONT
1 CONT In 1193, Henry married Agnes (died 1204), daughter of Conrad, Count Palatine
1 CONT of the Rhine. Around 1209, he married Agnes (died 1248), daughter of Conrad
1 CONT II, Margrave of Lower Lusatia. He had the following children, all from the
1 CONT first marriage:
1 CONT
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Henry (1197–1214)
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Irmgard (died 1260), married Herman V, Margrave of Baden
1 CONT
1 CONT   * Agnes (died 1267), married Otto IV, Duke of Bavaria
