1 CONT Otakar I won both Bohemia's autonomy from the German king and the hereditary
1 CONT rights to the Bohemian crown for his house of Premysl. His title as king by
1 CONT the Holy Roman Emperor Frederick II (1212) all but extinguished the control
1 CONT of the empire in Bohemian affairs. Otakar's reign thus established the basis
1 CONT of a strong Bohemian state, which was to reach the height of its power in the
1 CONT 13th century.
